review.review_text: Loved the youthful energy of this bar .....needed to pay 500 extra extra to watch live band performance upstairs. It's great value to see the artist in such intimate settings. The cute girl with tattoos collecting the money for the entrance fee was astonishing helpful, friendly, and polite . Yet when some of the expat crow became rowdy, she really took control  of the situation to control the rowdy expats quickly....... Listening to jam, this jam session was incredible....need more people like this in the world. Bar staff was young and efficient....in serving up my thirsty old man needs.....Rock on Revolver.

Good bar to meet new people. Had outdoor and indoor space which is nice cause it gets busy later at night. Upstairs plays live music, usually have to pay about $400 to get in. Life hack: If you just stand at the door and put your ear against it you can listen for free. I just saved you $400 sucker

The vibe is indie, relaxed but kind of loud. Good place to meet foreigners and get a drink or listen to live music. There's also a happy hour with affordable prices. There's a lot of memorabilia around, which is cool but maybe a bit more light could be nice. Service was neutral.

Good place for hangout and have a drink, they serve craft beer and wine, we both choose and were satisfied with craft beer there.
This place offer live music on the 2nd floor but you need to pay entrance fee to join live music it costs $400NTD.

Bartenders and staffs can communicate English so well. Reasonable prices

The drinks are good. During happy hour they are pretty cheap. The service was good and fast and the servers were polite. However, if you are looking for a place to sit and have a drink and relax, this is not the place (unless you arrive early). There are very limited seats. When i was there it was raining slightly so they didn't have any seats outside. There is a covered area outside to be able to smoke, there were 2 or 3 tables (but have to stand).
The music taste was nice but the music itself was a bit loud, therefore the bar got very loud around 22/23:00. The rumors are true tho, it is a bar where many foreigners go to (i am german myself).

Revolver is fine, but I wouldn't say it has much of an atmosphere. It's more of a place tha facilitates having a drink but doesn't do anything extra. Most people are actually drinking outside, on the street.

The beer selection is pretty good, with both Taiwanese and foreign beers available in the fridge by bottle or can. Seating is very limited.

Upstairs is where the live music happens, but with the price being 450NTD when I went, I wasn't tempted at all. It's way too expensive.
Happy hour until 9.30 Good music. Mix with locals, expats and tourists. They let people smoke after 100m, which turns many people off, who just leave. Upstairs music venue for a fee. Good place.

Amazing live music and good vibes. Great place for locals and internationals alike. The performance stage upstairs was cozy and intimate. NTD 400 for the show and a drink included. We saw Mike Tsai & Electric Soul band @miketsai.electricsoul, subbed by Allen @zhonzi - their energy was infectious and were all around great performers. The drinks seemed a bit watered down.

We felt very uncomfortable being in the bar. People were smoking cigarettes right next to us, indoor smokers everywhere. Apparently, indoor smoking is permitted at this bar. It was a small place with only a few tables by the bar on the main floor.

Cheap drink! You get what you pay for!The place is good for people who don't mind smelling like cigarettes from head to toe when you walk out of the bar.

Overall, we wouldn't recommend this place.
I brought my mom to have a good time but the service was terrible. They looked at us in a very downgrading way and they were extremely racist. I don’t recommend it for foreigners.

Akses mudah pinggir jalan. Begitu masuk wangi kaya dupa, trus menunya, cuman saran aja lebih bagus pakai kaca ya untuk menunya kalau pake plastik agak burek gitu jd keliatannya kurang bersih. Suasana indoor nya sumpek, pengap, jd pilih yg outdoor, tp banyak tikusnya karena saya takut banget sama tikus jadi parno makan sambil naikin kaki ke kursi. Karena liat ada tikus muncul2 di bawah jembatan diatas kolam renang, trus ada suara2 curut sama banyak jebakan tikus, jd was2 banget. Toiletnya juga gelap kurang bersih. Untuk makanan ya lumayan beragam pilihannya untuk rasa biasa saja, ayam bakar dan ayam gorengnya keras. Semoga bisa lebih baik. Terimakasih
Rasa dan tempatnya enakkk! Kalo pulang dari sini jangan lupa ngebungkus kopinya, enaaaaak. Ambience nya jawa bangett dapet, dihibur juga ada nyanyian live music jawa 👍🏻👍🏻

Sekian lama baru tahu kalo ditengah kota jakarta di wilayah kuningan ad rumah makan dengan model yg etnic seperti ini.

Kalau di lihat dari luar, rumah makan ini hanya kelihatan kecil,tetapi ternyata salah. Begitu luas area di dalam nya. Terbagi buat yg suka merokok maupun yg di ruang ac

Masuk ke awal kita disambut dengan pramusaji yang menggunakan blankon (jawa bgt ya), di kiri kanan bisa kita lihat banyak sekali hiasan2 yg ad disekeliling nya. Oya ad jamu penyegar juga lho diberikan gratis buat pengunjung yang datang. Di area tengah akan kita temukan berbagai ornamen2  etnik, ad juga kopi kekinian. Tak lupa hiburan keroncongan juga ad disana, siap menghibur tamu yg datang. Dibagian belakang makin rame lagi dgn ornamen macam2, spot yg bagus buat berpoto3. Yuks ajak keluarga kita mampir kesana, dijamim seru, senang dan kenyang

restoran yang unik, dengan makanan khas jawa sebagai makanan utama. desain resto dengan banyak ornamen klasik. membangkitkan suasana tempo dulu.

This is a hidden treasure cove in the bustle of the city. There is a lot of similarity in the food and the ambience. Both are brimming with surprises and have a lot to explore.
Some interesting choices for vegetarians too.
Home cooked Javanese food served in a splendid ambience. Must visit if you happen to be in Jakarta. I hear it's a one of a kind restaurant.

Adem, family friendly, tradisional nan sendu. Makanan enak. Masukan saja utk kolam di sekitar, mesti lebih sering dibersihkan, spya nyamuk2 tdk nempel ke kaki tamu. Hehe. Overall enak, ramai, banyak pilihan, sambelnya pedas, bapak yg nyanyi jg adem suaranya (fyi: jgn lupa utk mengapresiasi seikhlasnya bapak yg menyanyikan tembang merdu dan memainkan alat musik dgn apik yah). Cakep deh

Urusan rasa makanan sih juaranya
Harga jg sangat bertanggung jawab :D
Tp karena memang konsep tempatnya artsy2 javanese gitu, jd banyak ornamen2 unik n anehh. Sampe tetiba ada sesisir pisang digantung di atas kepala :D

Selalu ngangenin dan recommended! Sampe selalu lupa foto2.

Tempat yg nyaman utk Nongkrong baik dengan keluarga atau teman. Outdoorsnya sangat Instagramable banget. Cuman kalau datang di jam makan dan ingin duduk di outdoor kadang harus menunggu karena penuh. Utk rasa makanan cukup enak. Harga sesuai. Minuman beragam...

Tempat yang sangat unik, makanan beragam, beberapa menu terasa sangat pedas, cocok untuk suka makanan pedas. Suasana sangat hangat, dateng kesini pas menjelang senja. Harga beragam sik, untuk menu yg dipesan dibawah ini memakan biaya sekitar 250k. Pelayan sangat ramah dan cepat. Sangat rekomendasi untuk kumpul keluarga dan hangout bersama teman...

Very popular place serving home cooked Javanese style food. Very good spread of choices to choose or order from menu. Hard to get a table .especially during weekend. The place is decorated with a lot of distinctive decor and memorabilia. Restaurant was converted from an old house with a swimming pool and courtyard. Very nice cosy and laid back place for dining and chatting with friends and love ones

review.review_text: Staff at door are rude and discriminatory. DJ switched genres way too much. But it’s quite a nice place. Beer not too expensive.

The staff at KOR are professional, amazing at making cocktails and so friendly. We visited for a week and this was our first stop on a Tuesday in Taipei for cocktail bars. The ambience is casual, but decor and look are classy.

Would highly recommend if you’re looking for a nice place to sit, chill and drink. Had the Wu Fashioned!!

First time here as a solo traveler. Amazing atmosphere, service, music and drinks!
They also have locker storage to store your bags for 30 Taiwan yen as I came with a heavy backpack. The front desk ladies were also very helpful.
The bartenders, Tim and Vincent, were very welcoming. It was very easy to meet people and make friends.
Thank you guys so much for a great experience. I will definitely be back!
Shoutout to Stephen from Flare bar for introducing me!

Cocktails are pretty nice, but the waiter and waitress service pretty suck. Seems like they don’t really appreciate female customers. Better fix their attitude.

[updated]
After having a couple of drinks, we went to the dance floor and start dancing as a small circle, not blocking anyone’s way, but the waitress just walk through us right in the middle and bumped into some of us without any apologies.
It was like u don’t deserve respect if u don’t have a box, even if everyone of us did order drinks.

Great place to grab a drink after dinner.  Greeted by Tim and Vincente and their service was remarkable. Tell em what u feel like having and they will make the right drink for you.  Atmosphere is great with great people.
Upscale night club lounge with quality cocktails and music. Good vibe. Great music. Famous in Taipei.
Nice cocktail and service, staff are super friendly!

The mood is super nice to enjoy with friends or alone as well. Because people who are here are interested in making new friends!
The drinks and service for customers are  also great 👍 I'm satisfied with it!
If I come to Taipei again, I will definitely come here!

One of the greatest, if not best bar/club/whatever in Taipei.  Everyone is used to a place with good drinks but horrible service, great service but horrible atmosphere, or great atmosphere but horrible drinks.  Yet KOR has it all.

The bar staff seem more out of a bespoke classic bar than a venue with bumping music and fried chicken (which is awesome, btw).  Well thought out and tested drink recipes, along with skilled, professional mixologist make for a combo that can't be beat.

One positive thing I must say about Kor is that they play fantastic music. It’s like a mixture of old school and current jams. Very well done! Now onto the reason why I gave it a 3! It’s usually way too crowded and they can be quite strict about things. Like we had a friend who clearly wasn’t feeling well and needed to sit down for a moment but the security guard kept telling us to pick her up. I know it wasn’t ideal for her to sit in such a crowded space but we were trying to find the rest of our friends so we could go home. It was only for a moment. He could have allowed it. And the other thing was that it took about 45mins to 1 hour to get a drink. Other than that I don’t mind Kor, it’s a good looking bar slash club!
Tempat makan dengan banyak pilihan menu, cocok untuk makan bersama keluarga

Tempatnya enak utk keluarga, rasa makanannya juga pas ( ga keasinan ) jd bikin kita tambah pesanan terus, walau lauknya pakai piring kecil itu m'buat kita jd bisa menakar kebutuhan akan mknn itu.. tp sayangnya di tempat yg smoking area gerah bgt. Walau ada tempat terbuka ada baiknya minimal dipasang kipas angin di beberapa tmpt..

Pelayanan super cepat dan super ramah.
Yang paling amazing disini adalah nasi panas, sambal terasi dan iga bakar. Juara!

Sebenarnya ini bukan sekedar warung tapi sdh lebih dari Rumah Makan. Hidangan yg tersedia lbh menyerupai hidangan dari daerah jawa namun lbh terasa pedasnya.

Yg menarik dari tempat ini adalah banyak barang antik yg dapar di lihat dan disentuh. Rupa2 bentuknya. kamera, tongkat, porcelain, sepeda, motor, boneka dari kayu sampai besi,  berbagai lukisan, pakaian dan barang2 yg sepertinya  ingin menunjukkan bahwa pemiliknya telah keliling ke berbagai negara. Memang pemiliknya adalah ex-pejabat bumn. Tempat ini juga sangat cocok utk selfie.

Makanan enak, suasana nyaman bagj mereka yg menyukai berbagai pernik - pernik antik serta diiringi musik tradisional. Masukkan sedikit uang utk pemain musik, mereka akan gembira. Enak juga berlama lama di sini.

Tempat makan lumayan agak tertutup, tapi dalamnya luar biasa menakjubkan. Rasa makanan yang dipesan semuanya enak. Kalau kangen masakan buatan ibu, rekomend datang ke sini. Apalagi ada live music keroncong nya "juara" 😍
Good food, excellent services in MJS. Restaurant with live music. Masakan jawa dan sangat homy

Udah lama banget penasaran, pas lagi stay di daerah setiabudi akhirnya nyobain kesini dengan jalan kaki..

Diluar ekspektasi, makanannya enak enak banget😭😭😭 will be back sih pastinya!

Tempatnya unik. Bagus.  Bersih nyaman.
Pilihan menu banyak.  Untuk rasa cenderung asin tp selera sih.  Porsi pas
Pelayanan baik.  Semuanya ramah dan tanggap
Harga sesuai dengan apa yg di berikan

Untuk hangout sama keluarga cocok bgt, menu makanan ok, utk harga standart ga terlalu mahal bgt, kami ber 15 habis nya 1,2jt udah makan sampe kenyanh & udah ngopi. Tmptnya ditengah kota jd hangout ga perlu jauh2 dr rmh ☺
Makanan prasmananan khas Jawa yang ada di sekitar setia budi, lokasi strategis. Menu lengkap, tempat bagus dan tempatnya enak.

This is a speakeasy bar hidden behind a coffee store front. It's cute and intimate.

To order a drink, you tell the bartender what flavors you're looking for and they will provide you with a few options.

Honestly it was disappointing. They basically have a menu in their head and will not do anything too creative and it's just classic cocktails where you can swap out some ingredients. It would've been much easier to order if they just had a menu.

When we went there were only a couple people inside.  The staff were awesome and it was really interesting not having a menu since it forces you to try something new.  The drinks were amazing.  It was also a pretty short walk from the MRT and the night market is just across the street so you can stop by before or after getting a drink easily

I came here after seeing recommendations for Ounce on both Google and Yelp. The service, ambience, and drinks did not disappoint. I only wish I had more time here to become a regular as I'm only in town for a week. Would definitely come back. If I only had enough time in Taipei for one bar, this would be it

Really great bar service. I Don't do sugar or juice but the bartender was able to make me a really tasty "mojito" that was completely sugar-free.  Sat at the bar and it was easy to chat with other people and make new friends. 10 out of 10 for service, 10 out of 10 for atmosphere.

The review was based purely on the service quality. I came back here after three years hoping to visit the bar I used to like. Wow what a shock. The woman who lead us in got so offended by me asking if there’s a cocktail with a Taiwanese twist. She said, “This is an American bar.” Emphasizing American with her super strong Eastern European accent. Looking around.. this is definitely not an “American” bar since it’s not a sports bar. I told her I live in the States, then she started saying something else because frankly she looked like she just flew in from Russia. Sadly, the service was awful. It took half an hour to get the check. She didn’t even come by. We had to walk to the bar and pay. Thank god they didn’t ask for American tips lol. Never again. I walked to “Bar Without” just around the corner. A million times better with great service and great cocktails!

Vibe is great, cocktails are even better
Highly recommend the drink 20th century
You will not be disappointed!
The bartender here is very talented and the owner is a pleasure to chat with as well
Strongly recommend this bar

Short: nice snack options (few options but still great quality). Come here for the amazing drinks made by knowledgeable well-travelled bartenders within the calm and comfy speakeasy atmosphere.

Long:

One of the best speakeasies for english speaking expats to feel the calm soothing comfort of a dim-lit room, kind bartender service, soft-spoken jazz and high quality cocktails made specifically to your tastes.

Chinese locals should definitely come as well, either for a comfortable noise-free drink space with your friends/date, or to explore quality cocktails in an atmosphere parallel to wonderful speakeasies around the world (it helps to speak english, but there is also Chinese speaking staff too so no worries).

Best to come before 9pm if you want absolute peace and quiet and a guaranteed seat. Past 9, the crowds start arriving.

The bartenders make you what you want (no menu), and will make sure what you get is what you desire. If it isn’t, they will insist on remaking the drink for you, free of charge.

Ash, one of the bar managers, was a kind man from France who has traveled around the world and speaks great English. I had the privilege to have a nice conversation with him about random things of life on an early weekday night.

His kind service made me feel like I was back home, celebrating winter as i drank the hot spiked cider I ordered. And his knowledge of the drink is worth the price they ask. Learned a few new cocktails to add to my personal list of must drink again thanks to him.

Out of all the bars i’ve been to in Taiwan, this would be the one i would visit again if i had only one more chance to drink for the holidays.

And if health and time permits, I will be coming here again.

Thank you Ash and staff!

lovely speakeasy with very enthusiastic bartenders. the shop front was so misleading as you cant hear the music along the streets at all. may not be easy to find but just ask the dude sitting by the door. enjoyed the “no menu” setup:)

We were a big grp and were required a 2 drink min each, which we didnt mind. The drinks were very slow to come out though so we ended up staying longer than we wanted to, mostly just waiting. Drinks were ok, but pretty basic. Mostly just the classics with an added ingredient for a "twist". Having no menu was quite difficult.
My favorite bar of all (of the world). Amazing cocktails, great food and just wonderful staffs that understand all of your needs precisely. Super recommended ❤️

review.review_text: Lewis and Rachel are absolute gems to the place! Amazing ambassadors for not just Taiwan but the entire night life scene. Do yourself a favour a lookout for them if you’re English speaking and need to understand Taiwan nightlife

Fun spot downtown—especially for English speakers. Everything here was in English and all the staff spoke English as well great music, extremely unique cocktails (priced at about $300-$450NT). They have standing bar space for walk ins, otherwise you had to have a table reserved to sit at the booths inside. There was a $5000NT minimum to sit on the outside patio.

They have a cute spot for pictures, free air hockey and the drinks were fantastic!

Went here tonight with 3 friends, and the staff was ridiculous. We just came from Xmas dinner and I had a box with leftovers in my purse. We were asked to show ID and one of the male staff at the door looks into my purse and announces that we can’t come in with food or drink. I tell him clearly that this isn’t “food”, it’s packed away leftovers from a dinner. He keeps repeating that we can’t eat it inside...yeah, duh. It’s a wrapped container of leftovers. Lol This is after he LOOKED INTO MY BAG. Then he demands I leave my bag in a locker that I have to pay for, because apparently I’m going to take out leftovers and eat them at the bar or something? (He also accused me of having cookies..it was truly a bizarre experience.) Finally we were let, sat down, then told at the entirely empty establishment that we couldn’t sit at the table but had to sit at the bar (could have told us when we entered?) Then, to top it off, my friend was poured the world’s smallest glass of wine: photo below.

Would not ever go back again. They are ridiculous and lack commonsense.

I’m pretty impressed by the hospitality and politeness.

The lady host did her job promptly and was knowledgeable when asked for recommendations on cocktails.

Bartender dropped a glass accidentally and was politely apologetic, something which you don’t see at most of the bars/clubs.

Atmosphere was pleasant, prices were acceptable.
Definitely be back.

Came here on a Sunday and sat at the bar. Got a nice drink though a bit weak for the price (I think about 400 nt$). Gave me the run-around about The Den. Dark and "cool". Expect to pay a lot if you're looking to have a few. There is an outdoor patio. Live music when I was there (after 10pm).

Upscale trendy bar with a giant foosball table and pool table. Good for groups. Some creative cocktails. On the pricey side. On the night I went several guests threw up but the staff reacted swiftly and cleaned the mess up in no time.
I came here on Friday night. Good cocktails, good music, hip hop music, good service, good environment.
The barcode is now more like a clubbing area. The bar area used to be called The Den is now called Bar24 and it has a train theme. Drinks are pretty good.
Superb bar with excellent cocktails. Great place! Has outdoors too.

We went here on a Saturday because it was the only place that didn't have a ridiculously long line outside. Good entry price at 600$ including 2 drinks, except it took 20 minutes to get a drink.
The atmosphere was good but this place was completely let down by the terrible bad staff. I was shocked and so disappointed with the service. Instead of taking orders from the line of people waiting, one girl was taking snapchat videos on her phone and standing around looking dumb. She had her phone in her hand the whole time. To get served I had to wave my drink token in her face to get her attention. Instead of making drinks and taking orders 3 bar staff were stood waiting at the end of the bar talking and eating snacks. I understand if they were hungry but don't eat in front of customers who are waiting to be served, go out back and take a 5 minute break. I thought it was rude and lazy on such a busy night. They should of been moving around that bar swiftly and getting stuff done. When my drink was ready after 15 minutes of waiting, it was sat on the bar for another 5 minutes before the person who served me came to pass it over to me.
I did have a good night but it was let down by the bad service.
If you guys love spicy, should try their 'ayam setan' and standby with water 😂

Suka banget dengan suasananya...berasa hommy. Jd asyik bgt buat berlama2 disini. Dan poin plus buat saya pribadi...lokasinya dkt ktr jd anti macet kl mo mampir kesitu. Pegawainya ramah, makanannya jg relatif enak dan byk pilihannya. Cuma mgkn ati2 tuk yg sensitif bgt sama makanan pedes...pilihannya terbatas.
Restoran seng njawa buanget.. come there, you gonna have a very different atmosphere of south Jakarta. see for your self, then the food's so delicious.

Salah satu restoran yang beberapa kali saya kunjungi, baik bersama keluarga maupun teman. Saat masuk, kita dapat mencicipi aneka jamu yang disediakan dalam gelas-gelas kecil, gratis. Menu di sini kebanyakan masakan nusantara, lebih tepatnya masakan Jawa. Prasmanan, kita tinggal pilih nasi putih atau nasi merah, lauknya kita pilih apa saja berikut minumnya, nanti dicatat ama pelayan yang mendampingi saat kita masuk. Nama masakannya unik-unik, pun dengan minumannya. Selalu pesan es teh manis di sini, karena gelasnya porsi jumbo. Beberapa tandan pisang yang imut (pisang emas kali ya) digantung di dalam restoran, bebas untuk kita ambil. Demikian juga kerupuk plastik yang ada di meja, itu bebas kita nikmati. Rasa makanannya enak.
Pilihan makanan banyak, rasanya enak, interiornya serem. Menilai berdasarkan taste makanan karena rawonnya enak

review.review_text:
Very chill standing bar with beverage in reasonable price! So fresh and tasty!
Inna is really helpful recommending flavors of the drinks! She’s really nice and hardworking staff here! Btw, she’s very pretty too!

Great little bar with pre made cocktails on tap. There is another level in the basement.

Second floor has more craft cocktail options.  Not quiet speakeasy (it won’t impress any cocktail connoisseur. If you are, I would skip this place and go hide bar or ounce.  藏 Hide Bar Bar >>> ounce) but not bad for what it is.

super awesome spot, definitely a must try if you love interesting cocktails! staff are really warm and friendly. you can also get a small sample of the drink you’re interested in and ask the staff for suggestions. drinks are delicious, have different alcohol levels and surprisingly affordable! 😋

Cocktail on tap but done right!
We have had cocktail on tap or bottle before, but they never tasted right.
But Draftland 10000% did!
We ordered two drinks, one 13 & 16 - one rum and one gin based both with different fruit.
You can 100% taste all the incredients they listed and they all work great together.
Candidly, if I was not told it was from tap, I wouldnt have guessed.
You do get a buzz after 1 drink and it was just the right level of alchol to not be overbearing.
Loved it! Go!!!

Original draft land. Lovely time. Very interesting layout that keeps the interesting experience throughout the night.

Definitely recommend going up to their testing room.

Don’t judge a book by its cover~
This is best describe my personalised cocktail~ made by bartender, Ian.

If you can speak mandarin, service staff Yi Rou 以柔is a great host.

If you love cocktails and surprises Draftland is for you. Creative draft taps with no beers.

Nice spot for drinks. It is super crowded so make sure to get a reservation if you want to sit upstairs. The drinks are nice, they have some unique flavour combos for sure. I liked my old fashioned for sure!

Their first floor has cool, reasonably-priced draft cocktails with standing room only, but their second floor has a "testing" menu and limited seating!

On the second floor, each person will need to order at least one drink, and the price seems like it depends on the day because the menus change, but ran at 400 NTD on 1/10/23. Definitely interesting drinks up here, though, and worth a try!

Per their recommendation for a sweet drink, I got the #7, which had earl grey, masala, and rose. This was definitely the right recommendation to make for me - super sweet, but with complex flavors. The earl grey, masala, and rose gave me pause on paper because those all seem like super strong flavors, but they worked together oddly well and left me with a taste that's difficult to describe! It's sweet, full-bodied, and leaves you with a curious aftertaste that keeps you coming back for another sip.

My partner ended up getting a custom whisky drink because their testing menu at the time didn't have any whisky drinks. It ended up being a black tea old fashioned, which he described as "very good." I thought I smelled a sweet aroma from the drink (turns out it might be from the distilled osmanthus, sweet vermouth, cinnamon leaf, or all of the above?), but the taste was sweet, strong from the whisky, and with an interesting aftertaste from the black tea and sweet vermouth.

We went down to the first floor after, and had a final drink before heading out - the drink with rum, coconut, mango, pandan, and grapefruit was SO GOOD - sweet, creamy, and easy to drink. The pandan flavor was super present, and so were the fruity flavors. It was dangerously easy to drink... They also have a basement floor with bathrooms, standing drinking room, and a little Draft Land drinking board game (unfortunately, they don't sell them...). We loved it!

Each floor had its draws, but Draft Land is definitely worth a visit!

Chill and nice atmosphere. Cocktails were impressive and awesome with cheaper price(compared to other bars in Taipei)! You can have a drink with friends at 1F or go upstairs enjoying special cocktail. Friendly service. Even you can taste the cocktail before ordering. But very crowded on weekends.

Love the vibe!
staff is quite helpful in explaining the mix, they are also open to recommend good bars around if they don't cater a specific niche alcohol you are looking for.

Tempatnya tidak terlalu besar tapi cukup nyaman. pilihan menunya sangat banyak. rasa makanannya lumayan enak. pastikan untuk reservasi tempat terlebih dahulu bila ingin datang pada jam makan siang karena ramai dan tempat parkir terbatas.

Suamiku suka banget sama tempat ini :), vibesnya ditambah ada keroncong, dan alhamdulillah ada mushola juga, nyaman tempat sholatnya, barokallahu moga lancar, barokah selalu usahanya :), makanannya juga enak :)

Makanannya enak2!! Ketika datang langsung disuguhkan bermacam2 lauk, kita tinggal memilih lauknya.
Suasananya juga enak, vibes jawa jadul~
Kalau disiang atau sore suasana agak menyenangkan, namun di malam hari agak gimana gitu.

Makanan enaaaak, banyak pilihan juga. Makanannya disajikan di wadah wadah dan ada penghangatnya di bawahnya, seperti prasmanan gitu, tapi ga langsung ambil. Jadi kita bisa lihat makanannya langsung dan pilih yang mana yang sesuai selera. Nanti tetap diambilkan sesuai porsi yang kamu pesan.
Harga ga mahal sih, cukup terjangkau.
Penamaan menu makanan dan minumannya lucu.
Yang lebih asyik lagi adalah tempatnya, pilihan tempat duduknya bisa di dalam atau di luar. Yang di dalam ada musik tradisionalnya gitu, konsep Jawa. Yang di luar ada kolam (mirip kolam renang tapi gabisa dipake renang ya). Ada yang duduk di pinggir kolam dan di atas kolam, semacam gazebo gitu. Overall so good!

food was nice.

the resto seems a bit spooky. front area abit dark.

Buat suasana t4nya bagus veunya, tapi agak terlalu kecewa ma rasa masakannya, padalan sy pesan menu yg pedess semua seperti ayam setan,sambal demit n cumi hulk tapi satu ga ada rasa pedass"nya😂 emank dasar kuliner jawa rasaa pedesnya boong belaka🤣 masih ada manis"nya.

Udah jadi wishlist buat ngunjungin ini. Cuman baru bisa terwujud baru-baru ini. Jadi ini berlokasi di setia budi. Pertama sampai ke lokasi kayak gak yakin sih sama tempatnya. Namun sekalinya masuk suasana jogja langsung seketika menyergap. Aroma ruangannya enak kayak menyan atau melati gitu kurang paham juga yanv penting enak. Interiornya bergaya jadul gitu dengan sentuhan kejawaan. Jadi pas masuk langsung ada kasir setelah itu ada smeacam meja prasmanan dimana tersedia menu yang beragam. kita tinggal pilih ada yang udah mateng ada yang perlu di masak lagi terlebih dahulu. Setelah menentukan baru kita ke tempat duduk. Makanan akan diantarkan. Terdapat smoking area dan nonsmoking. kami memilih smoking area karena tempatnya lebih rindang. dan di smoking itu doong suasananya bener-bener kayak bikin kita bukan seperti ditengah kota. rindang. pepohonan. syahdu. sejuk. ada kolamnya. Nyaman banget deh. dan teduh banget gitu. Solanya tertutup dedahanan pohon ya g ada disitu. Untuk segala pernak perniknya lucu-lucu. untuk makanan dan minuman imdisini termasuk murah banget siih. rasanya juga lumayan enak. Tersedia toilet yang nyaman juga. Ada juga tempat ibadah di lantai atas. Sumpah ini tempatnya nyaman banget, dan unik banget juga terdapat beberapa spot yang lumayan untuk berfoto. Ada live music setiap malamnya (video terlampir) Pokoknya juara sih. Berasa di raminten deh serius wkwkkw Tempat (kursi) yang berada diatas kolam sih yang selalu jadi rebutan.

review.review_text:
I recently visited The Shrine bar and overall had a good experience. The atmosphere was lively and the staff were all very friendly. The drink selection was impressive and I enjoyed the gin tonic I ordered - the flavors were well balanced and the gin was top quality.

However, I did have one issue that took away from my experience. The bar has a 90 minute limit on table occupancy. While I understand that this is a common practice at bars and restaurants to keep things moving and make room for other customers, it was a bit frustrating to feel rushed and have to purchase an additional drink in order to stay longer.

Aside from this issue, I would recommend The Shrine bar for a night out with friends. The drinks are tasty and the atmosphere is lively. However, be aware of the 90 minute limit if you plan on spending a longer evening there. Four stars.
Nice bar with happy hour all the way from 3 to 9, featuring iconic taihu 925 lager. The vibes is special with all the spirit worldwide. People are also nice there.

enjoyed the eclectic and unique decor and all the drinks we tried were great. the shrine sour was my favorite. as it was new years eve, we received poppers for the countdown and it helped to provide a festive atmosphere
Really nice bar! Aesthetic was amazing with designs and illustrations from all over the world, creating a very unique space.

+ : great happy hour! From 4 to 9pm, 130nt a lager or simple cocktail, great decoration, great toilet, chill music
- : potato wedge seems from frozen industrial pack with no taste, pay first policy not cool

I wasn't impressed at all. All I wanted to do was sit down, enjoy a beer, and read my book.  I was told that the house policies limited me to two hours in the bar, and I had to spend a minimum  of NTD300 ... which is quite expensive for a beer in Taiwan.

absolutely to recommend nice place professionals in service and delicious drinks warm atmosphere outside places for smokers also happy hour in the late afternoon perfect for a break and chilling moments

I have tried Piña colada and Negroni here. The cocktail-making technique of the bartender is not bad. I like the cocktail that I had ordered here. The price of the cocktail is not high. The selection of tapas here are not too many and it taste ok, not too impressive.

It's basically our local! It's open from early afternoon till late. They have the best happy hour in town...NT120 for beer, wine or spirits. The vibe is cool and there is indoor and outdoor seating. They also offer tasty snacks. Definitely good for groups but also great if you want to have a coffee and chill.

Really good experience at the Shrine!
Felt like I traveled the world browsing through all the pictures and decorations!
We visited on Saturday night, wasn’t too crowded so it was really comfortable!
The drinks were good as well, staff was really kind and polite, definitely recommend it!

*remember to make reservation before going😉

It's a great place if you are craving for javanese food. Their meals are super delicious. Great ambiance too with the javanese decorations and keroncong music. Once you step in, you will feel as if you're in Yogyakarta.

Menu yang disajikan banyak pilihan
Nuansa jawanya sangat kental
Parkir luas
Tempat makannya bisa reservasi via Zomato
Harganya juga worth it
Harganya lumayan mahal, tetapi makanannya enak, jadi kangen dengan masakan Jogja. Suasananya juga khas Jawa banget, banyak barang-barang yang antik. Cukup sekali-sekali aja makan di sini.

Indonesian restaurant with vintage javanese concept. The place is decorated with various items which are look like personal collection. The presentation of the food feels homey. They also named their menu with unique name (Indonesia Ghosts). Price is in mid range. If you love spicy food, you should try their ayam setan and sambal! And not forget to mention, they also sell Kopi Bu Lurah.

Semua makanan yang disajikan enak. Pelayannya pun ramah dan menyenangkan. Kurangnya ada di lahan parkir, tidak ada lahan parkir khusus ke resto ini. Kemudian area musholla plus kamar mandi yang kirang baik dan kurang bersih. Semoga owner kedepannya memperbaiki area ini
Tempatnya mantap banget, ada live music jawa, banyak spot foto juga, makanannya murah2, pelayannya ramah2, pokoknya best banget lah buat nongkrong dan buat sekadar makan

Very unique restaurant with Javanese concept. Their foods are homy and tasty. Located in the middle area of Jakarta, easy to reach.

If you ever go to House of Raminten in Jogjakarta, this place is best for you to have the same experience,

review.review_text: Fun airport-themed bar with innovative, aesthetic cocktails!
19 hours Bar and restaurant hopping in Taipei. I try coffee Negroni. Surprisingly! Is one of the best Negroni!

We arrived into Taipei a week ago.  We found out about this cool new bar in central Taipei with an airplane themed environment so we decided to go check it out.  WOW!  What a place!  A MUST SEE!  The front of the business looks like an actual commercial airplane!  Big swinging airplane door and all.  The whole bar is an actual runway and I was told the numbers actually have significance to the TPE Airport.  If you are in Taipei, make SURE to stop in.  Make sure to ask for Jimmy the manager and he will make sure you are very comfortable.  Great drinks & food!  The fries are delightful, with some secret ingredient applied.  When asked what it was, they told me they'd have to kill me if they told me!!  :-) LOL.  Go check it out.  GREAT PLACE!!!

Really nice bar with an aviation theme, the cocktails were all very tasteful, well balanced  and unique, the bar tenders look like they really know what hey are doing and there's a good vibe. At the moment there's a special going on with 2 drinks for the price of one, which makes the already cheap cocktails (+/- TWD320) even cheaper!

The bar also has a small food menu, which is like the cocktails unique, I've tried the Mexican fries which were great.

Customers are a mix of Western and Asian aircrew combined with local students and workers. All in all a great bar I can certainly recommend and next time when I'm back in Taipei I'll visit again!
if you miss flying during COVID, you’ll love this airplane-inspired lounge. plus the drinks are good, popcorn is complimentary, and it’s not so crowded you can’t have a good chat.
I love this place so much!!! The staff is so friendly and the cocktails are good enough! They can get all you want to you. Definitely recommended this place. I’ll back again soon!!

The first time I went to this bar, the atmosphere was amazing. Jeremy was really nice and friendly, and even let us do some karaoke at night (he had a microphone and used YouTube for the tracks).

After that, I went two more times and couldn't find Jeremy. The other bartenders weren't nearly as friendly, and the service wasn't nearly as good. There was also a strong smoke smell. I don't feel like coming back again.
Great place, very nice and comfortable atmosphere. The bartenders are very attentive, the drinks are good.
There are Ron Zacapa (my favorite Ron) and many more choices to enjoy a good drink with friends 👍

This is one of the best bar experiences I've ever had. They are always so welcoming and want to make your experience at this bar, one of the best experiences ever. If you don't like your drink will make you a new one at no charge. I've even met the owner and head bat tender and they were so amazing and nice and helpful. I feel like home when I'm at this bar and will return any time I am in Taipei.
makanan nya enak, tempatnya juga tenang dan sejuk. harus cobain kopi bu lurah ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Saya memesan ayam pakai sambel ijo. Saya berikan rate : 7/10
Ayam cabe setan : 6/10
Soto daging : 7/10 karna kurang panas saat disajikan pada saya. Jadi rasanya kurang pas, garamnya juga kurang berasa.
Sayur pepaya : 6/10. Kata mba nya sih udh di olah dengan baik agar tidak terlalu pahit. Tapi saya merasakan masih sangat pahit.

Untuk yang mau kesini boleh datang sendiri ataupun rame-rame dengan keluarga.. Tempat untuk duduk pun beragam.
Ada indoor dengan banyak hiasan antik..

Outdoor nya bener-bener cheerfull. Ada di meja, banyak pepohonan, ada kolam ikan nya juga. Ada di ayunan juga loh.

Serta kebersihannya sangat terjaga

Tempat nya unik, namun menyeramkan. Maksudnya baik dengan dekorasinya, namun sang king banyak ya mereka juga mengikat banyak debu. Jadi banyak barang seperti koleksi topi, koleksi pernak pernik dan lain lain, namun banyak debu dan tidak bersih. Suasana juga gelap dan kurang terang. Butuh lampu dan penataan ulang.

Makanan nya lumayan enak namun penyajiannya menurut saya kurang baik. Seharusnya mereka bisa menyajikan nya lebih higienis. Lalu semua masakan tidak menggunakan peng hangat dan mereka masak ulang atau hangat kan ulang. Jadi kalau gorengan menjadi sangat basah. Terlalu banyak minyak. Kalau makannan jadi tidak Fresh.

Untuk variasi makanan banyak, sangat makanan rumahan dan Jawa. Tidak semua makanan nya enak namun kalau mau pesan mendoan pesan nya satu saja kan porsi nya besar. Harga bisa dibilang juga cukup mahal. Dan dari segi pelayanan, posisi tidak ramai pun masih lama karena harus di hangat ulang dan di masak ulang.

Tempatnya cozy,  walaupun etnic jawany kental bgt dgn desain interiornya.  Lebih prefer yg outdoor atau smoking areanya siy.  Tapi sayangnya pas kesni mgkn kemalaman ya jdi bnyak makanan yg udh abis,  jadi ya pilihannya terbatas.  Tapi buat rasany cocok buat lidah orang Jawa Tengah kaya aku,  enak pokoknya.

Makanan yang ditawarkan sangat Indonesia dan cukup beragam. Ada area smoking Dan non-smoking. Area non-smoking dipenuhi benda2 etnik tanpa kesan menyeramkan sama sekali. Ada band keroncong yang memainkan lagu2 yang menambah suasana menyenangkan. Ada mini coffee bar juga untuk kalian yang suka ngopi.

Makananya enak,cm harganya klo bisa dikurangin kwkwkwkw
Tempatnya sih unik banget ,tapi sayangnya dtg pas malem udah gtu ujan , jadi ga bisa foto2 dehhh

Kalo untuk repeat order mungkin next time lah yaaa karna jarang lewat sini

Tempatnya dengan nuansa jawa dengan alunan musik keroncong. Harga makanannya sekitar 10 ribu sampai 50 ribu. Tergantung pilihan. Saya merekomendasikan kopi susu bu lurah dan bebeknya enak. Untuk kerupuk dan pisang gratis dan bebas ngambilnya. Ada non smoking dan smoking. semoga bermanfaat

Tempat makan siang bareng temen kantor apalagi kalo ada acara ultah / farewell kesini deh pasti.
Ada jamu dingin welcome drink, variasi menu yang banyak dan area makan yang unik di area semi outdoor dan ada mini pool di tengahnya.
Konsep resto yang traditional artistic menambah kesan indonesia banget.
Overall cuma 1 parkiran nya g luas langsung vallet aja deh klo ada petugasnya, untuk harga ya lumaya sesuai dengan rasa.
Recomend , makanan enak dan bersih.

Warung makanan serba Jawa yang cukup unik. Variasi makanan yang kreatif dari pemilik / pengelola yang dipadukan dari penelusuran dan pengalaman kulinernya!
Makanan2 didatangkan dari daerah aslinya atau dicopy dengan citarasa sesuai originalnya akan menunjukkan bahwa Jawa pun punya aneka masakan yang lezat!
Didekorasi dengan pernak pernik yang unik menjadikan sensasi tersendiri.
Ada iringan musik keroncong dengan pilihan lagu masa kini ataupun lagu lama nostalgia menjadikan restoran ini dikunjungi dari segala lapisan dan menjadikan kesan yang tak terlupakan!!
Sebaiknya reservasi dulu untuk bersantap dengan keluarga atau kolega karena pada jam makan siang atau jam makan malam cukup sibukl dan ramai pengunjung!!
Karena parkiran terbatas,  anda bisa minta parkir valet yang tarip sukarela!!

review.review_text: Best craft cocktail bar. Expansive selection of made to order cocktails, very unique pairing of flavours, excellent descriptive menu so you know what you’re getting. The price is very reasonable for the quality of cocktail you’re getting. English speaking staff, helpful. Very busy during evening, recommend you call in to reserve a seat before coming. I definitely will plan a visit again whenever I’m in Taipei.

Delicious and creatively crafted cocktails await you at this place. Sitting by the bartender this time, watching them work is truly enjoyable. The staff is excellent and friendly, guiding us to appropriately portioned dishes, minimizing resource waste. They recommended a delightful local whisky, and the small birthday surprise was truly charming. We'll definitely be stopping by again next time. 🥰💕🍹

I prefer the stir ones over shaken ones. In general, the drinks are well crafted , also they have a nice story to tell about all drinks. On another side, it without too much surprises. I also ordered some good, especially the chicken wings: so many pieces ! I can’t finish them all

I’m not one to drink or enjoy bars but I can hands down fully recommend this bar to anyone who wants to have a good time and enjoy carefully thought out creative drinks. We made a reservation ahead of time and Daphne was our bartender for the night. The music selection was great, the drinks were great, and Daphne was just the most special person to talk to! Everyone was so accommodating - and you can tell the working relationships between the bartenders themselves was great. The menu was really intricate with all personalized drawings and explanations for each drink. Presentation was 💯. We will definitely be coming back when we visit Taipei again. And thank you to Daphne again for your hospitality!

Really interesting cocktails featuring ingredients from Taiwan. Felt like it was very whiskey heavy (as are many bars in Taiwan). Great vibes, sat at the bar and my friend knew the bartender so got many free shots. Try their butter shot– it’s surprisingly refreshing and not too sweet! Would definitely go again.

Managed to book a table last minute for NYE dinner. We were so hungry, we ordered the ramen and chasu rice for dinner. Then had some finger food and drinks! The jalapeno cheese is my favorite and goes well with the refreshing cocktails they offer 😋
Food was far under par, I only had an appetizer and was very unhappy with it, first wait staff started to give it to the couple next to me. The drink I had was amazing but not worth the trek

A fancier, slightly more upscale bar featuring well crafted mixed drinks.

When we visited, there was a guest bartender for the week. This meant that they had a quite limited menu with only 4 options. The drink I got was fine, but I probably would have preferred a normal night.
Love the hospitality at this place, Expertly crafted cocktails are must do at every visit. The newly extended shop space makes it easier to get seats too!

Well, we have 5 days in Taipei and this is our second time here. The drinks are absolute 💯🤌 The staff are friendly and ✨wonderful ✨Totally worth your visit. They are pretty popular, especially on weekend so make sure you book your table.
Mendoannya juara dah ini 🤣🤣buat masakan lainnya standar aja ga ada yg memorable, cuma vibes nya enak dinner disini, buat harga masih affordable ga overprice 😋

Ini adalah warung yg jual makanan sunda yg enak di Jakarta , harganya pun tidak terlalu mahal menurutku. Untuk yg pertama kali silahkan pesen Ayam Setan. Pedesnya nikmat, gurih, ayamnya empuk. Aduh ini wajib deh. Untuk udangnya jg enak dan gak trlalu pedes.

Gak rekomen pesen nasi uduknya (kurang wangi menurutku) sama bakwan jagung (agak beda sama bakwan jagung manado ya)

I love it! Warung MJS is a hidden gem. The food here is absolutely delightful, and the atmosphere is cozy and inviting. The flavors are authentic and remind me of home-cooked meals. The service is warm and welcoming, making each visit a memorable experience. I can’t get enough of the delicious dishes they serve. Highly recommended!

Sumpah ini restoran jawa yang menurut aku hidden gem di Jaksel sih. Banyak menu masakan jawa yang rasanya menurutku enak dan juga minuman yang disediakan bervariasi. Kita bisa pilih menu langsung di depan karena konsepnya prasmanan, tapi kita bisa milih lewat daftar menu juga. Konsep interiornya autentik, antik, dan menurutku suasanya fotogenik banget. Ada area outdoor juga di belakang dekat taman. Untuk harga menunya standar sesuai rasa dan porsi. Tempatnya mudah dicari tersedia lahan parkir juga. Kemarin pas dateng sempet waiting list karena area makan di dalem ga terlalu besar

Overall ya not bad lah ya..
Makanan lumayan enak...
Suasana sore maybe lebih asik, kemrin saya dateng ud agak malam jam 7 gitu. Jdi gelap gelap agak horor ya haha..
Pelayan bnyk jd lumayan respon cpet..

Harga ya maybe krena daerah ny kuningan juga kali ya
Jdi harga standart bagi kuningan ya lumayan ya..
Lumayan pricy..
Sambel 13 rbu belom service dan tax hehe
Belom dapet sambel walau ud order ayam goreng

Warung MJS adalah warung dengan sajian makanan terbaik sejauh aku tinggal di Jakarta. Menu lauknya sangat variatif, dari tempe mendoan, aneka olahan ayam, sayur mayur, dan es campur. Rasanya sangat unik, khas dengan cita rasa makanan rumahan.

Makanan yang paling menarik perhatian adalah Asem-asem Daging, dagingnya begitu lembut dan rasa asem yang segar. Selain itu, Sayur Pare yang diolah baik, tidak terasa terlalu pahit, dicampur dengan ikan teri kecil. Sungguh nikmat!

Pelayanannya begitu cepat dan tanggap. Pemilihan meja tidak dapat bebas, harus mengabari staf di depan. Hanya bisa menentukan ingin smoking atau non-smoking.

Tempatnya sangat unik sekali, tidak ada yang sama di setiap sudutnya. Dalam 1 meja, terdapat 1 kursi dengan desain berbeda dari 3 lainnya. Terdapat kolam dengan jembatan. Di jembatan, ada gong yang bisa dibunyikan. Dari depan terlihat kecil, namun di dalam begitu luas. Aku rasa bisa menampung 40 orang kurang lebih.

Pakirannya agak luas untuk mobil, di depan warung. Namun jika kurang, parkir juga bisa di pinggir jalan ditata oleh Pak Tukang Parkir.

Harga makanannya masih masuk akal. Untuk makan 2 orang dengan 4 lauk dan 2 sayur, seluruhnya Rp. 250rb. Pembayaran dengan QRIS tersedia, jangan khawatir.

Tucked away behind the concrete jungle of Sudirman skyscrapers, there's this hidden restaurant serving humble Javanese food buffet spread so you just have to choose what you wanted to eat. The price of the food was reasonable so choose as much as you can eat. The place has this eclectic and old school vibes with traditional Javanese ornament. There was a band playing keroncong music when I visited. Taste wise the food I ordered like fried milkfish, egg, tempeh are all quite good. Would still recommend the place for a reasonable price and the novelty of the interior design.

Warung MJS salah satu bukti nyata "don't judge a book by its cover". Dari luar kayak rumah kayu ukuran kecil aja, ini jadi salah satu minusnya, parkiran yang terbatas. Jam makan siang antri, nunggu sekitar 10 menit sampai akhirnya masuk. Pilihan menunya banyak, udah pasti masakan jawa, mulai dari yg manis sampe pedes menampar. Di awal masuk lgsg bisa liat pilihan lauk & sayur. Pesenan kita ngga ada yang failed sih. Rempah, manis, asinnya pas. Cumi hitam cenderung manis, ayam setan yang pedes dengan aroma sereh, oseng mercon kikil yang ngga abis saking pedesnya sampe ke ubun2, udang balado yang pedas gurih, dan tumis daun pepaya yang masih terasa bitternya. Untuk es teh, standarnya ukuran gelas jumbo. Nasi uduk & nasi putih ngga ada rasa yang berbeda, sama aja :)) untuk suasana di deket area jembatan adem banget kena semilir angin. Walaupun yaaa ada serangga kecil yang terbang di area makanan. Overall, akan balik lagi ke tempat ini kalau lagi pengen makan pedas menyiksa.

Authentic Indonesian, should I say, Java vibes. Love the atmosphere.
The food’s taste too, mostly like home-made delicacy. Brought two of foreigners friends of mine here and glad they are knowing the taste of what home made foods taste like. Moreover, in the middle of Jakarta.
The place is so neat and clean.
They also have many varieties of traditional dessert (with ice).

Datang saat jam makan siang, rame banget jadi harus nunggu lumayan lama buat dapet tempat duduk.
Tempatnya cukup nyaman, banyak dihiasi ornamen-ornamen khas jawa, dan ada live musik keroncong.
Makanannya ada berbagai macam menu masakan rumahan, ada ayam, telur, oseng-oseng, dll, seperti warteg. Untuk harga segitu yaaaa rasanya lumayan lah, gak ada yang spesial kecuali harga dan nuansa jawanya.

review.review_text: AMAZING! I stumbled upon this place with my friends and had so much fun. The beer is yummy and affordable. The service is what puts this place on top though! The workers are so kind and warm. (Also the workers speak great English, so it’s helpful to us foreigners) The music and atmosphere is great too. I’d recommend this spot to anyone visiting Ximen who wants a drink 🥰🥰😍😍
Pub is homey and the vibe is very laid back. As a filipino, i really liked their taiwan beer (number 1). I like it more than our homegrown beer. Highly recommended

It's really hard to find a draught beer bar in Taiwan and yeah, this is the one, they offered plenty of draught beer selection.

The bartender is friendly and nice. You can ask him if you have any questions.

Price wise is still alright, if in taipei, as the alcohol in taipei is all about the same price

Overall it is not bad, but extra point if you are looking for draught beer, else it's all cocktail bar

I’m on a three day trip here in Taiwan with my friends and we found this nice spot to drink on our first day. We had to go back here on our last day to try their other craft beers. My experience here is really one for the books because of the good vibes this place brings. 💯

Cozy place. Good beer. However there seems little  food option, and  I wish there would be more selection for draft beer.

I had the Milk Porter, really cacao-y.
Cozy bar in Ximen with draft beer. Interesting Taiwanese brews and lovely service. During the week not overcrowded. Note: you have to spend at least 300 NTD per person!
Very hip and chill beer gem along the night market. The ambience is so giving. Perfect spot if you want a peaceful time alone or with friends!
Great place enjoying beers Taiwan local, IPA from all over the world, and great hospitality opening over midnight..!! Highly recommend when visiting Taipei. 👌 😍😍🍺🍷

Great small craft beer place in the middle of Ximen. Six different mainly Taiwanese craft beers on tap plus many more in cans and bottles from all over the world in the fridge. Reasonable priced. Great and chilled atmosphere and wonderful service. Very recommended!
Leslie was very nice. She can recommend the drink I like. She very very friendly ❤️

Legit javanese restaurant in Setiabudi, Central of business area in Jakarta. Sebagai salah satu perantau jawa bisa dengan yakin bilang rasa makananya legit rasa jawa sedeppp. Ayam setan, cumi jederr, oseng terong dan ga lupa mendoanya yang super legit. Bisa dengan bangga ngajak tamu dari luar pulau/negara yang pengen ngerasain masakan jawa di jakarta. Reasonable price for all the great food and ambience you’ve got here.

The food has java authentic taste, sweet and savior. Recommend to eat with family and kids or friends reunion. If you like spicy try their “ayam setan” to challenge yourself. In the weekend there also “Keroncong band” performance too.
Makanannya cukup enak, ga lama. Tp musholla nya kurang rapih

Sudah 3 tahun tidak mampir dari terakhir kali ke sini.. pernah makan mie jawa rasanya biasa aja. Kali ini kami mesen menu sayur lodeh, sayur daun singkong, ayam bakar, 2 nasi uduk, cumi saus tiram, sambal setan.. minumnya teh tawar panas dan dingin serta es kopi susu. Total tagihan 207.000 dan bisa dibayar dengan QRIS.

Makananya enak2 jawa tpi pedasss,banyak pilihan nya dan harga masih masuk dikantong,cmn klo kesini lbh baik jgn pas jam makan siang ato klo gak booking dl by phone .krn ini ruameeee bisa2 smp sana nanti disuruh waiting list,dan untuk parkiran dia agak susah

Really love the decorations, so vintage all over the area.
You have to make reservation first especially on weekend during lunch or dinner time.
Foods taste are delicious and affordable.
There is also live music.
Might come back here later for kopi susu and kue cubit
When we came here we took the queue first, then got a non-smoking place, but in my opinion the place was a little dark with little lighting (is it really like that?), the food was pretty good

Paling juara mie goreng jawa, rasanya mirip dengan mie petruk yg tersohor di cirebon
Mie godog jawa lumayan rasanya
Tempe medoan juga enak.... selalu saya order tiap kesini
Sambal setan juga mantap pedasnya.. enak
Sayur krecek juga enak
Ayam cabe ijo juga enak

next mau nyicip kopi lurah yg katanya enak juga. info kuliner subscribe youtube channel : JAKARTA EXPLORE (huruf besar semua)
The restaurant serves tasty Javanese food, some of them very spicy, with a unique decor. The price is reasonable with quick service and lots of seating. Parking is a bit of a challenge.
Truly a hidden gem. Tucked behind offices and what nots, this place has a small village charm and tasty food to boot! The mendoan, Ayam Setan, Mie Godhog, and Gedang Kadhemen is to die for!

review.review_text: OriginBAR in Taiwan is a true standout in the local bar scene. The star of the show, without a doubt, is Blair. Blair isn't just a bartender or a host; they're the heart and soul of OriginBAR, ensuring every guest feels more like a long-lost friend than a customer. Blair's exceptional service makes you feel right at home, while the tea-infused cocktails are an absolute delight. A must-visit for anyone looking for a memorable night out with unique drinks and fantastic hospitality!
Great bar. We enjoyed the cocktails that were excellently prepared. Staff was very friendly and the environment was welcoming

Personally prefer food than tea cocktails. would like to recommend handmade potato chips and pan-roasted vegetables.
We had three different tea cocktails. Most of them had a fruity flavor and the alcohol was a bit strong. There was also a noticeable bitterness in three cocktails, which  personally guess may be caused by the way the tea was infused.
There’re lively and noisy. They have a special activity at 9 pm on Friday.
Travelled on May 2023. They serve varieties of good cocktails and nice fries. The lady boss is very good service and friendly. Lady boss treated us extra shots. The environment is good.

What a magnificent find! Very walkable from the MO and quite a gem, down a small alley off the main road. They specialize in tea cocktails, I had the Pou Chong Tea Cocktail for something less sweet. Perfect blend. I’ve had a decent amount of good cocktails in SF and this bar’s mix craft is definitely up there. Service is above and beyond. I think service levels in asia are generally quite high but the bartenders and servers here are incredibly friendly and helpful. Food was excellent as well, we got the dumplings fries and some linguine. Menu is expansive, there’s sure to be something to your tastes. Excellent little cocktail bar

Best hospitality, great bartenders and service staff. Stumbled onto this bar while heading to another bar and decided to give it a try. Walked in without reservation, got a bar seating. Dimly lit with cool vibes, yet it has a welcoming feeling. Minimum spending per pax. Ordered the classic Negroni and it was one of the best. Bartenders are knowledgable and friendly. We were served  free shots of their tea infused alcohol, and served another Japanese whisky based shots when we were leaving. Definitely will come back!

Taste :4.4/5
Environment: 4.3/5
Service：4.6/5

OriginBAR is a hidden gem located in the heart of the bustling city. As you step inside, you are greeted by an elegant and chic ambiance that sets the tone for a delightful dining experience.

The restaurant also has an impressive selection of tea style cocktails that are expertly crafted by their mixologists. The OriginBAR Signature Cocktail is a must-try, a refreshing and fruity drink that will tantalize your taste buds.

The place is cozy and warm just like home. Staff provide warm hospitality and the service is excellent. There are multiple creative cocktails here and the decorations on the drinks are beautiful. Bartender is good at cocktails made by tea and can provide drinks based on your flavor. The taste of the cocktails is really good! Great bar for relaxing and drinking.

Great atmosphere but a little bit dark inside. Tea-based cocktail was their house specials. They usually treated everyone with a shot of tea liquor (for free). There was a minimum of NT500  per person. Staffs were friendly but always remind customers that time is up.

Some of the most delicious tea and fruit based taiwanese cocktails i’ve ever tried. Thanks to Ken’s phenomenal service and detailed recommendations for cocktails based on each of our taste preferences

Sebenarnya ini bukan sekedar warung tapi sdh lebih dari Rumah Makan. Hidangan yg tersedia lbh menyerupai hidangan dari daerah jawa namun lbh terasa pedasnya.

Yg menarik dari tempat ini adalah banyak barang antik yg dapar di lihat dan disentuh. Rupa2 bentuknya. kamera, tongkat, porcelain, sepeda, motor, boneka dari kayu sampai besi,  berbagai lukisan, pakaian dan barang2 yg sepertinya  ingin menunjukkan bahwa pemiliknya telah keliling ke berbagai negara. Memang pemiliknya adalah ex-pejabat bumn. Tempat ini juga sangat cocok utk selfie.

Makanan enak, suasana nyaman bagj mereka yg menyukai berbagai pernik - pernik antik serta diiringi musik tradisional. Masukkan sedikit uang utk pemain musik, mereka akan gembira. Enak juga berlama lama di sini.

Tempat makan lumayan agak tertutup, tapi dalamnya luar biasa menakjubkan. Rasa makanan yang dipesan semuanya enak. Kalau kangen masakan buatan ibu, rekomend datang ke sini. Apalagi ada live music keroncong nya "juara" 😍
Good food, excellent services in MJS. Restaurant with live music. Masakan jawa dan sangat homy

Udah lama banget penasaran, pas lagi stay di daerah setiabudi akhirnya nyobain kesini dengan jalan kaki..

Diluar ekspektasi, makanannya enak enak banget😭😭😭 will be back sih pastinya!

Tempatnya unik. Bagus.  Bersih nyaman.
Pilihan menu banyak.  Untuk rasa cenderung asin tp selera sih.  Porsi pas
Pelayanan baik.  Semuanya ramah dan tanggap
Harga sesuai dengan apa yg di berikan

Untuk hangout sama keluarga cocok bgt, menu makanan ok, utk harga standart ga terlalu mahal bgt, kami ber 15 habis nya 1,2jt udah makan sampe kenyanh & udah ngopi. Tmptnya ditengah kota jd hangout ga perlu jauh2 dr rmh ☺
Makanan prasmananan khas Jawa yang ada di sekitar setia budi, lokasi strategis. Menu lengkap, tempat bagus dan tempatnya enak.

Pretty traditional decoration inside with Indo cuisine. You can also find all kinds of historical Indonesian stuff, like wayang and primitive artificial toys as well.
All servants are really friendly welcoming you. Since the interior passway is not so wide, all staff there will give you the way for you first while passing through them.
Indonesian cuisine are all delicious and my wife told me most of flavors are from Jawa Tengah. I think it is ok since sweety and spicy mixture are what I feel there.
Drinks and ice mixing bowl are tasty too. All are traditional flavors. Multiple mixture of juices or drinks there are recommended since you can have various feeling at that time.
As for the interior decoration, I think the owner tries to express different kinds of atmosphere from countries he/she visited before. It likes the melting oven filled with Eastern and Western cultures. You can find all the specific collections and enjoy there directly.
Foods are economical and like it's name. It is Warung expense.

Tempatnya ternyata cukup luas di dalam...atmosfir berasa seperti bukan di Jakarta dengan interior vintage ala2 jawa bahkan ada pertunjukan musik tradisional jawa. Kalau malam digigit nyamuk karna restonya open air. Saat nanya ke pelayan ada menu paketnya atau tidak hanya dianjurkan sistem buffet...tinggal pilih yang kita mau lalu makanan dipanaskan kembali sebelum disajikan di meja...rasa makanan not bad lah...tidak ada label harga terpampang dimanapun! dan lumayan mahal: nasi+1 macam lauk+sayur+1 side dish (belum termasuk minuman) kisaran 70-80rb'an per orang.

Good place to have lunch with your partner.
It has good ambience. This is Indonesian authentic food. There's Indonesian ( Java ) traditional vibe inside the restaurant.

review.review_text: Randomly found this bar on map during my first days in Taipei and lucky to take a seat without reservation in a Saturday evening. The bartender is nice and recommended me drinks for my needs. Good to start with ‘Beginning of Prohibition’ (wrapped with newspaper) which tastes fresh and light. Also had a ‘Heart of Aztec’ and it has a bit of smoky taste. Kinda secret and chill vibe in busy city center. Would definitely visit again if I go to Taipei next time!

Nice speakeasy atmosphere, staff was very nice.
Drink were properly made and tasted good.
I like the touch with the entrance and the fact that there is no sign at the original entrance.

Bookcase and second floor, almost easy to miss, but we got lucky! Inside of another restaurant and bar we made our way to prohibition in the states..I mean Taiwan. Haha. Great look and ambiance, attracts a lot of western tourists for sure. Cocktails were pretty straight forward, nothing special, nothing boring, but just right in the middle. Staff was friendly too.

So so hidden. It's actually inside of MQ. Ask any staff, they'll direct you up. This is what speakeasy should be like, I feel so taken care of here. Everyone's chatty and friendly here. A bit of a wait but I didn't mind. Oh and the secret door to the bar, slides left away from the other wall. Good luck finding this gem. It's worth the trouble.

I ordered their Chrysanthemum Fizz and there's an actual chrysanthemum on a orange peel placed on my drink. (See photo) Everytime I take a sip, my nose would get very intimate with the flower and peel. A subtle but intoxicating fragrance would fill my breath and taste. Absolutely magical. My favorite drink thus far. Alcohol taste is minimal too, for a wuss like me.

My favorite of this bar, aside from amazing conversations and the diversity of its customers, is their soup. I don't know if you can actually order it, but late into the night, they would give out chicken broth in a shotglass-sized copper mug.(see photo). I was so confused at first but after shots and drinks, this well warmed up broth was simply heavenly. I did make me feel better overall. Body was warm, my heart was warm.

The Alchemy bar must be Taipei’s best hidden secret. For sure you will not easily find it if you haven’t been there before with friends or haven’t studied the Google reviews in advance. We were lucky to ask at the Opium Champagner bar on the corner of the building. The bar tender kindly showed us the way through the entrance of another venue called MQ. After entering the MQ you will have to take the stairs on the right to the second floor where you will end up in dimly lit hallway. After a little while not knowing where to enter or where to knock a sliding door magically opened to the Alchemy’s classic bar room and it felt like traveling back in time to the prohibition era. This is our cocktail flight on that evening:
1. Beginning of Prohibition, well balanced, entering the universe of mixology
2. Chrysanthemum Fizz, actually turned out to be my favorite, the refreshing and subtle taste drew me into the lounge chairs
3. Green Lake, obviously an all time favorite with the ladies, light in alcohol and full summer flavors, why would anyone order an Aperol Spritz that has been extremely popular in Europe during the last years, when you can enjoy a beautiful summer drink like the Green Lake
4. Alpine Meadows, I enjoyed the mellow taste of the tea infused gin and the warmth of the Benedictine, but the burning tea leaves on top were a bit too much
5. Kingston Negroni, this drink put me back up on my feet, I love the strength and bitterness of a classic Negroni, with the coffee it rushed right into my veins.
It has been a great evening at the Alchemy. I only wish that we would been seated without any restrictions since we were the first guests when arriving at 8pm.

Came on an extremely busy day with a few conferences and mixers so service was a bit slower, but I didn’t mind. The bartenders were rushing to get everyone’s drinks made in an orderly fashion, which they did well. It took a bit of time but each drink was solid.

Cocktails are expensive (~$400 NTD) but delicious and quite strong compared to others I had in Taipei for the same price. Really cool atmosphere, and you enter and exit through a false bookshelf that slides out of the way. The bartenders were very friendly and gave great recommendations for other restaurants and bars.

Favorite speakeasy bar in Taipei. They’ve got whatever you want. Classy, modern fusion with fresh ingredients blended. Drinks are tasty. Bartenders are professional and friendly. I love the bar seats and the smoking area. Smoking area is semi outdoor with Marquee view. Love the choice of music. Love the vibes. Absolutely love it here.

Although Alchemy used to be one of the better cocktail bars around it hasn't quite kept up with the competition. Prices (~450ntd) are hard to justify when better cocktails can be had plenty of other places in Taipei. It was also absurdly loud last time we went - nearly lost my voice trying to talk to my friends.

The space reminds you of winter. The fries with truffle mayo and chicken tender were really good.

The cocktail I had had strong wood tasting notes. The alcohol could have been more complex but it was still a nice drink.

Really friendly service. Overall good experience.

I have been abroad for a decade, and once I got back home since last October 2023, I have been here three times! Warung MJS was on the top of my restaurant list that I wanted to visit in Jakarta. Their food still tastes the same, their atmosphere is still the same, but the modern-minimalistic-look coffee station that they put in the middle of their restaurant is kinda ruined the whole theme of this restaurant’s vibe.
My favorite javanese restaurant in Jakarta. Love the nasi uduk with the fried onion, ayam setan, ayam wewe, sambel demit, ikan wader, terong. Pricey but I really love the food. Still worth it.

lokasi strategis dekat SMAN 3 Jakarta dan MRT Setiabudi. menunya banyak, pengen cobain banyak tapi takut kemahalan HEHE. paling enak makan di deket kolam renang biarpun smoking room. harganya lumayan lah, rasanya juga enak. tapi sayang air kolam renangnya agak kotor.
Tempat makan yg rekomendasi sekali dan wajib utk didatangi bersama keluarga atau teman krna mknannya enak2 dan suasana yg unik.
pilihan makanan super banyak dan enak. Desain restonya unik. Kerupuknya free!!! Ambil sepuasnya

Wuenakkk puolll meski fanasss didalem.

Makanannya wuenak harga rada mahal

Yang dateng kece kece, mobil mewah mewah,

Dari dlluar kelihatan sempit tapi setelah masuk ternyata lebar juga.

Dalemnya juga banyak barang tempo dulu.

Kalau pesen pedes ternyata beneran pedes ati ati pesen sedang saja drpd keringetan gaes

Mi and my familia so enjoyed.
makanan enak..anak2 suka ..thx
Makanannya enak, kemarin ada kesalahan kelebihan bayar, dikembalikan sih cuma klo take away harus dicek sendiri supaya ga bolak balik complain

For those, who like Indonesian cuisine, MJS can be an option.

Before the pandemic era, the MJS is a place to stop by waiting for 3in1. now maybe it will be a different story because it has turned into odd-even.

Its vintage concept with a traditional Javanese atmosphere instantly makes the heart feel comfortable. The presentation of okulele and bass sounds as residence music. Make u feel like home.

For the price it depends on how much you want to eat, but what is clear is that it won't be more expensive than eating at pizza hut or fast food restaurants.

the place is quite large for "Warung", it is popular for groups to had the sspecial occasion here. For large groups you have to book in advance to be able to dine in here.
The food is average, and the service is ok. The indoor seating area had many rooms since it seems this place used to be a residential home. This place has many artistic articles such as statue wall decoration

review.review_text: Best Bar near the Shangri-La Far Eastern, drinks are awesome and they make a killer Old Fashion so we’ve been ending the night by sticking the landing MaryLou Retton Style and having an old fashion to wrap the night off.

I think it’s the best Irish pub in Taiwan! Great drinks, great atmosphere, great decorations, price around 180-200NTD so it’s similar price like any other place in taipei, if you want the best Guinness and best price trust me it’s here.

I go back to this pub quite often, it’s casual  and feeling relax, it’s really just like a real pub, if you go out Taipei more you will see it’s not easy to find a real pub just walk in  to grab a beer. ( most of the bar they ask you to wait until they allow you to)

If I want to just grab a beer after work, or a casual weekend, I definitely choose this place. They often have some events and also live music, must try.

價錢跟台北其他酒吧差不多沒特別貴，180-200台幣左右，氣氛很輕鬆自在，常常會有樂團表演真的很愛
It’s a great pub to relax and watch live bands at the weekend… definitely recommended if you want to meet the opposite sex

Great bar, friendly bar tenders, biggest selection of Irish Whisky's I have ever seen in Taiwan, draft Guinness just like it was served in Ireland and the Cocktails, hmmm everyone should try. Wide selection of foods available, including stone oven baked pizza, fries, chicken wing's and drum sticks, much more.

Great decor, nice drink, friendly staff and wonderful atmosphere! The performance on Saturday night is highly recommended👍
Btw, I made the straw
Came here after arriving in Taipei and Ray gave us the best service as a bartender. Thank you Ray for making the birthday experience for my friend unforgettable. TAIWAN #1!

They don't show the correct drink volume on their menus. Heineken was quoted as 150 TW dollars for 500ml during happy hour, instead I got under half a pint. I told the waitress and she just said she would tell her boss, no offer to give me the correct volume or money back. So basically that works out to about £8 a pint in happy hour.... Rip off, that's London prices 💸
Friendly and engaging bartender. Serves the best wings and beer. Even discovered a new drink of choice baileys and milk.
Here on Christmas Eve, wonderful smell of Mulled wine when you walked in, excellent and more, one of the best Irish Coffees have had in a pub for years, and that's from an Irishman 🎄🤪😋🇹🇼🇮🇪🍷
Good bar

Buka puasa di MJS dadakan karena request dari temen. Tempatnya asli jowo banget ditambah ada live music paling enak sih diluar yaa udaranya sejuk bgt karena ada kolam renang dan juga banyak pepohonan, es susu kopi bu Lurahnya enak gelasnya pake gelas jadul
Awesome authentic Indonesian food which is frequented by locals mostly. Great ambience and service is fast and friendly.
Tempatnya asik dengan dekorasi khas jawa, saya baru pertama kali kesini pas makan siang, tersedia banyak tempat duduk didalam, menu makanannya pun banyak, saya suka sekali sama suasananya

Bagus, suasana Jawa. Dekorasi pernak pernik etnik jaman dulu dan mengingatkan pada Jogja sih. Makanan prasmanan, ada jg menu lain yg bisa di pesan. Menu minuman banyak pilihan. Cocok buat foto-foto. Karena tempatnya tidak terlalu besar jadi kalau waktu jam sibuk harus antri terlebih dahulu untuk menunggu meja kosong.
Ga suka karena beberapa menu cuman ada waktu malam, kecewa aja

I don't often give across the board 5 star ratings, but this venue deserves it.
Good food, fast and courteous service and an amazing atmosphere, with eye catching, interesting, and unique collection of  curios everywhere the eye can see

review.review_text: I ordered a drink from the magical book, didn't know what it was actually and it indeed magical. Themed pub with a themed menu. Didn't understand it fully but it was great

My friends and I love this place sooo much!! We were staying nearby and glad that we popped in to chill here. The interior has Anglican church feel. But what's most wonderful is how knowledgeable the bartenders are on the different types of cocktails and how friendly the service rendered. They want to know each customer's preference and concoct each cocktail according to his/her preference. Haven't experience such personalized service in awhile!!

This may have been one of my best night caps abroad. I found this bar after dinner by searching on the map and let me tell you that all 5 starts they have are well deserved

First, the Moscow mule was delicious. The bartender and the owner were extremely friendly (even if I don’t speak Chinese).

We had a long chat about Mezcal and Pisco (I’m Peruvian!). The owner had me taste Taiwanese whiskey and a few of the Mezcals he had. We shared a great moment together talking about the different cocktails around the world, especially those coming from LatAm.

The night ended with a shot of Mezcal.

Couldn’t have asked for a better night. It was the perfect wrap to my time in Taipei.

Strongly suggest you check this place out.

Thank you again!

review.review_text: I felt welcomed as soon as I stepped in. The waiters are super friendly, they actually engage with their clients. After a missed flight and lost hotel reservation I ended up at this place about 12:45.  The kitchen was closed, but the very kind and drunk bartender went back and made me a beef stew with bread that was fantastic.  The drunk and friendly bartender put away 3 red wines and 15 shots of Jameson and Tequila between 1am and 4:30am.  It was one of the most impressive drinking displays I have seen on my travels.  It was like the drinking scene from Raiders of the Lost Ark.  She ended the night totally coherent which was incredible.  This place is great with Christy Moore, Luke Kelly on the walls and Jukebox and a friendly group of travelers and expats.  A big thank you to Luna and Helen.

Very friendly and welcoming pub. Behind the wooden exterior lies a different world. Walls are plastered with pictures of Ireland. Incredibly snug and homely. Helen and her staff make your really feel welcome. This pub is many a mile from Dublin, but the pint of Guinness is exceptional

Else that, the decent quality of cocktails and food, where else can be better than here?

review.review_text: I stumbled upon a hidden gem in Taipei – a cocktail bar that exceeded all my expectations. The standout cocktail, "No Money," is hands down one of the best I've ever had. Each drink on the menu showcases incredible creativity, both in composition and presentation. The bartender is not only exceptionally skilled but also super cool and friendly, adding to the overall fantastic experience. If you're in Taipei, this is a must-visit spot for any cocktail enthusiast!

The tried "On Our Wedding Night" followed by 2 shots of super fresh Oyster from JAPAN (takes 20 mins, order early) then "Peach flavour wine". Everything is so delicious here! I bet it'll be packed on a weekend. Lucky I came on Wednesday. Less people could get my drinks in a few mins. Salute to the mixologist, very talented, creative, and detailed oriented. short version: great cocktails, uniquely presented and made, small but cozy, calm during weekdays(good for dates) and i imagine very busy during weekends.

Long version:
As a solo bar hopper, this place was very nice. I came early on rainy day, October 31st Monday, but because everyone parties on the weekends in Taiwan, everyone had probably stopped going outside on actual Halloween day. I was hoping for more people to talk to, but there were very few people and i can only speak English so that's understandable, which was fine by me. I came for the cocktails and they were nice.

The drinks were good and the presentation was beautiful and playful. My favorite was necromancy, loosely based off of a Chinese zombie it seems. Sweet, strong and very clean. The other I liked was in a recycle bin. Very funny and refreshing.

I ordered food and drinks enough for the bartender to give me a free shot, which was nice too. I'll definitely come back again.
