review.review_text: I’m trans and was welcomed by everyone and had the night of my life!! Everyone I met spoke English and the bar was smoke free. I went on a Saturday and they had dance shows and unlimited drinks. If you like meeting new friends and dancing this is the place for you. 💋

My first visit since the remodeling and it's so nice it's cool and not smokey now. The drinks were plenty strong, and while not a huge crowd, it was very positive, welcoming and fun. A couple performers too, and a super diligent staff. Def a step up from what it was and totally worth a visit

Not a lot of people even though there was an event, met nice people there and one of the dancers was really pretty but the music was too loud and the host speaking with the microphone was even louder, way too loud

We went on Friday night from 10:30pm-12:30pm. We only got one drink for free even though I read that it was All You Can Drink online. Our drinks were watery and they put ice in my beer.

They just announced the legalization of same sex marriage in Taiwan so I was hoping for a huge crowd.

10:30pm It was very empty and there was no DJ.

11pm DJ finally began. I think the music was better before the DJ started.

11:30pm more people began to show up, probably to get cheaper cover

12pm only a few people on the dance floor dancing but the club is actually getting quite full

Full of young women and locals. I didn’t see any foreigners, at least that I know of.

It is 800NTD entrance fee, all you can drink.
You can dance, chat, and enjoy yourself.
The day we went was pretty quiet but it’s because it was raining that night. The vibe is great music is okay and drinks were good. I’m an extreme light weight so the drinks were just fine for me, but perhaps for heavy weights, it would seem like they’re drinking water.
They had a cool event and it was pretty entertaining.
The only downside is that booths are reserved so you’d have to be standing the whole time unless you go outside and sit on the stairs to take a breather otherwise expect your legs to be hurting if you’re wearing high heels.

This lesbian bar is all u can drink for $800,u can dancing ,but the music is not what u think ,it’s 10 years ago music.
and DJ is not professional DJ.
the alcohol u never want try again.
😊maybe next time I will go “Wonder bar “or another lesbian bar but not here.

Had so much fun with my friends from different countries and bartenders were so friendly. Had couple of free shots too. Music here is also quite fun cause they don’t play something too deep or too club like. You can easily talk to other people in the club too.

I went here once on a Friday with some American friends. Paid 500 NT for unlimited drinks. Drinks were ok but nothing to rave about. Other reviews say the music is bad here but we went on a Kpop-themed night so I liked all the music.

Pros: The crowd is really friendly. After one drink I had a lot of fun dancing with my friends and 1 or 2 locals. I threw up in the bathoom around 3am and a girl asked me if I was okay (much appreciated). When my friends and I went outside we chatted with a group of locals from out of town, their English was really good!
If you can't speak Mandarin you should be fine.

Cons: Layout is awkward. I wanted to sit down but was told the large seating area was all reserved, but I didn't see anyone sitting there the entire night... (12:30-3am) The stools along the wall facing the dance floor are very sparse, most people are by the bar or hugging the wall if they're not dancing. Bar was kinda crowded, bartenders were a bit curt. I know smoking in bars and clubs are normal in Taiwan but the smoke is HEAVY in here.

Probably won't come back because I'm not into clubbing, but for a lesbian nightclub this place is not terrible.
Definitely coming back, TABOO is such an amazing lesbian bar. I feel safe and comfy whenever I come here. And then there are loads of entertaining activities to join too. Highly recommended!!! 🥰🥰

Place definitely has his own atmosphere, similiar to european gay bars I've been.in Berling and Russia. Tiny, smokey, questionable music - will be more fun if you go there with your big company or often visitor and can dig the atmosphere. Drinks cannot be good in such places

Very very nice roof top bar. The cocktails are fantastic and special. The perfect blend of sweet/fragrance with alochol taste. Suitable for men or women to savour. I ordered the 小熊甜心 and it was very very good.
Recommended by our taiwan friend and really love it. Drinks are not expensive,  perfect view, nice songs and vibe. 10/10

P.s. we went to other bars and was rejected entry because i was in flip flops. This store allowed me to enter. They mentioned men in flips flops is not allowed but ladies they can give us a chance 🥰 love the service
Really nice bar with amazing view and balcony area. Staff tried to not return my change but they did when I asked for it.

One of the best bars in Taipei, with an awesome up close view of Taipei 101 from the balcony and roof floor. Bartenders are friendly and easy going, and willing to customize a drink for you on weekdays. Please don't expect superb bar service during rush weekend hours, it's not going to be perfect anywhere else too. Music is okay, atmosphere is always fashion and chic. One of a kind experience!

Perfect spot for a nightcap, cocktails and drinks if you want to also lose yourself in the eclectic decor surrounding this interesting watering hole in Taipei. Cocktails at the bar outside on Level 9 seemed a tad bit below par. Bar inside looked like it served a meaner concoction. Service is good. Ambience is on-pointe. Rooftop lounge is very Instagram ready too. Definitely a bar for those trigger-happy wanderlusters!

Nice place for Taipei 101 view.
Chill place for drinks and dancing a bit.
Good vibe in general, only the cocktails are needed to improve..some taste are really awful..my friend can’t even drink it.
Terrible service, unfriendly digital menu and boring cocktails. But the food was good from other kitchen/restaurant, deserved two stars.

Frank delivers the upscale lounge experience with a balcony overseeing the famous 101 tower. Extensive bar with specialty cocktails, locating at the heart of many other different night clubs.

The food menu is above average, private booths and tables with more privacy are also available.

DJ booth situated in the center of the venue. Diverse customers, mostly English speaking or at least bilingual.

One of my default bars in Taipei with a mix of good vibe, view and staff. Service varies however.. and the drinks are strong, but not the best I’ve had. Plus point is that it’s a local hangout joint so you get a local experience.

Relatively crowded on weekdays, so it’s a good choice to soak in the feel, but do go early on weekends or get a table. I think they have quite some to improve in terms of the product.

Do try go level 2. It’s a good view/ atMostphere

Nice atmosphere and cocktails.

You can see Taipei 101 from the rooftop. A nice place to meet up with friends while seeing good view/enjoying the great cocktails and food here.

review.review_text: Cute vibes! I was in Taipei for a short layover and stopped by this bar before my flight. The bartenders were so friendly!  I ordered one cocktail off their menu, which was a cute Netflix looking app, and a second custom cocktail that the bartender concocted with one of the in house gins. Both were great. They specialize in gins, so if you're a gin person, you'll be fan. One of the bartenders also made me try a Finnish style gin (really good! I wonder if I can find it in the US) as a send off before my flight. Good service and cocktails, would come back again.

Really cozy place to grab a cocktail. I learned a lot about gin from the staff and tried variety of different drinks like the jungle bird, jasmine, and Negroni. The fun part was trying Finnish gin at the end of the night!

Cozy cocktail bar with a big focus on Gin- of which they have an amazing collection. Their cocktail list has some great inspirations from Taiwanese ingredients, and you can also request customized gin drinks by talking about your gin/drink preferences to one of the bartenders.
Very friendly service.

What an amazing cocktail bar!  I recently visited Sidebar on my trip to Taipei and was blown away with how great it is.  In fact, I’d say it’s one of my favorite cocktail bars that I’ve ever been to!

The atmosphere is great, the bartenders are knowledgeable and are super friendly and the cocktails are so amazing!

I got several drinks and my favorite was a gin variation of an old fashioned.  I’m a bit depressed that I live 7,000 miles away from Sidebar (I live in Colorado) and can’t visit again soon.  But, next time I visit Taipei, I’m coming back to Sidebar for cocktails!

If you love gin or are curious about gin, this place is a must visit in Taipei!  I was overwhelmed by the attentiveness and knowledge of the staff.  They really did all that they could to ensure I would enjoy my visit.  In the main bar, it is cozy and they have a fun and unique menu.  They use an app called Sideflix (I think created by the owner?) and it is a fun and creative way to order drinks.  For those who really like gin, it may be possible to go to the hidden bar behind a vault and password protected.  In here, the world of gin expands and you are able to try unique cocktails based off of a flavor wheel of gin.  They also go above and beyond in making sure you get what you want.  For example, I went with "grassy" as my first flavor and 3 unique gins were brought to me and I got to sample them before then choosing one and then receiving a unique cocktail that was a twist off of a Last Word.

This place is a gem and the owner and staff are so friendly.  It has my highest recommendation!

I love the bar when they know what they do!
Their menu is like movie theaters, so you can choose the film (i.e. drinks) you would like to try. So it gives you scores like rotten tomatoes.

But today, I tried just classics. The best to know the skillset and the entirety of the Bar's quality.

Negroni with Cotswold gin amazing.
Old-fashioned with Taiwan's proud whiskey, Kavalan, really good too.

Stir drinks are so great, and I have little doubt for shaking ones.

Two classics 1000twd. But it's worth it.
Amazing experience. Bartender is friendly and concocted a great personalised cocktail.

Hands down my favorite Gin bar.
Yung-Pei Kao is the sweetest bar tender. He made my drinks to perfection while teaching me more about Gin. I’ve always been passionate about Gin, but he showed me the different nodes that gets brought out at different Gin locations.

My official favorite is the rose water from South Africa. He made me a off-menu drink with egg whites and raspberry. I would 100% recommend it for those who don’t like too sweet drinks and prefer floral favorite things.

The vibes are pretty chill during the weekday, I didn’t have to wait too long for my drink and I had space to talk.

Other drinks I tried: Aviation (tasted blue :P) and Old Fashion Twist (tasted like yummy apple pie)

Overall, very clean place with a nice theme and great drinks.

I came back here for a second time and this time I made reservations for the inside bar. You get a special code to get in there and it's really cozy inside. You can't have groups with more than 4 people. They let you do gin tastings over here.

This time, the bartender asked me what kind of drink I'd like. I told them anything with egg-white and sour. He brought out different gins for us to taste in. I was with 3 other people so ended up having around 7 gin bottles with tasting glasses.

I ended up ordering a drink with the yuzu gin from Japan. It was delicious!

I accidentally came here for a drink but it  really exceeded my expectation. The bartenders were very friendly and they put effort explaining me about my drinks. They even showed me a secret room for gin lovers ( password required ). You should try traditional food of the bar, it was really tasty tho!! Highly recommend

A hip bar located in a relatively quiet street. This is definitely the place to hang out if you love gin - ordered silver gin fizz and gin tonic with monkey 47. Overall great experience and will definitely come here again.
Mantap tempatnya, tradisional banget. Cuman memang makanan masih biasa dan parkiran masih kurang

mantap warung MJS 😁😁😁 rasa makanannya luar biasa 😋😋😋 dominannya manis, tapi sambal bawangnya pedaaaas 👄👄👄 tempatnya enak buat nongkrong malam2 asal yg di taman berkolam dan berpepohonan 🌲🌲🌲 karna kalau didalam geraaah pisaaaan eeeuuuyyy... staff semuanya ramah 😉 soal harga boleh merogoh kocek ga terlalu sedikit ga terlalu banyak ya sedang-sedang saja 🤑

Kurang cocok makan sama keluarga dengan anak kecil 👨‍👩‍👧‍👧 karena disini semua tidak ada non-smoking area 🚭 tapi mantap kongkow bersama kerabat atau pasangan 👬👭

Restoran makanan Indonesia dengan desain dan interior Jawa kental. Direkomendasi oleh atasan saya. Makanannya enak-enak, banyakkk banged pilihan. Menu mutlak setiap kesini >> Telur Ahay (telur asam manis dengan sedikit pedas mantap), Mendoan MJS (khasnya MJS dan tempenya konon asli Banyumas, tempenya juga gede2), tempe bacem, Sop ndeso (sop kentang asli kangen rumah), sayur tempe sadis, Opor daun singkong (pecinta kuah opor wajib), minumnya es khilaf, makanan penutup pastinya kue cubit coklat matang (ajib).

Banyak spot foto, meja dan bangku ayunan, utk kopi bu lurahnya untuk saya kurang strong kopinya.

PS: jangan lupa ke toiletnya ya..

Saya hari Jumat kemarin tgl 17 Feb akhirnya bisa kesini lagi setelah covid ga pernah kesini lagi. Saya tetap pesan telor ahay (asli enak) + tempe mendoan (enakk) + sayur singkong (enakk) + sop ndeso (comforting) + nasi merah (tapi agak keras huhu) + orek + es bablas (ini mantap jiwa) dan tetap minum jamunya dong pasti ^^.
Mknan rasa rumahan dgn suasana remang2 krn dtng mlam2, blom sempet cobain kopi n jajananny. Keburu kenyang krn kalap. Enak walo too pricey

Tempat makan yang penuh dengan ornamen seni yang beraneka ragaman. Perpaduan Jawa dan sentuhan European arts. Dari pintu masuk, kita disuguhkan dengan beraneka ragam menu makanan khas jawa. Sayur lodeh, jangan asem, rawon, urap2, olahan ayam dan ikan, sayur daun singkong, dll. Jadi kita di awal disuruh pilih dulu plus minumannya apa. Nanti nya akan dibawakan ke meja kita. Bedanya disini, makanan yg kita pilih disajikan di piring tersendiri. Jadi bakalan puas. Tempatnya cukup luas dan di bagian belakang ada ruangan outdoor juga. Disediakan menu kopi kekinian dengan beragam jenis kopi pilihan.

tempatnya enak buat nongkrong, makanannya juga enak, dan mendoannya mantap, kesan pertamanya lgsg itu sih...

Menu makanannya yg cenderung "masakan rumahan" bener-bener bisa jadi "obat" untuk orang-orang yang ridu masakan rumah atau masakan ibu.

untuk rasa juga enak, ga yang sampe nendang, tp udah cukup mantap, terutama menu yg ada label pedas/cabe. Pedesnya mantep, tp bumbu dan rasa makanan ga ilang, jadi ga cuma dominan rasa cabai.

Dekorasi yang unik dan bisa dibilang eksentrik jadi daya tarik tersendiri, apalagi buat yang aktif di sosmed.

review.review_text: A great bar in Chung Shan area where most of the bars were Japanese bar. Atomisphere was excellent and most impressive part was the aquarium tank above the bar. So attractive. Bartenders were so professional and friendly. Drinks, food were super great. The only pity/question is personal drinking capacity limited the enjoyment of those great cocktails. Definitely will visit again.
Nice deco, love the aquarium and atmosphere inside. The customized drink is awesome, those on the menu are also fine. Good to take a try.

We happened to find this bar after dinner nearby. The atmosphere and decoration made us relaxed, and they served delicate cocktail here. We were lucky because the bar became full in a short while just when we got a table. The waitress were really helpful, and you might ask for their recommendations from various of choice. The price of drinks are just a little higher than normal bar, and they didn't prepare peanut, while you can order some side dishes, such as fries , onion rings or chicken. We did have a really good talk and enjoy the bar here, and it would be a good option for you wanna drink with friends on Friday night.

This place is wonderful but very expensive for Taipai. I am from NYC, so I am used to $12 drinks, but this is not the norm here. Don't get me wrong, they are wonderful and beautiful drinks, but you should know before you go. I think there was also a 400 or 500 Taiwan $ person minimum. Less on week nights.
The bar has a fish tank above it which was a fun novelty. The drinks were great. I had the black sesame drink with was unusual but delicious. We had the wasabi fries (great!) and the chicken (not memorable). The decorations are fun.
A fun place to go with friends.
Basement space is design well. Great music and laid back vibe. Lots of cocktail options. Sesame one is the winner!

One of my favorite bars in Taipei!
They offer excellent service, food, and drinks!
Me and my friends always have a wonderful time here.
I love the vibe and the bartender !!
Last time i decide to celebrate my birthday night by myself.
and it was the best decision i've ever made!
thank you. 珍珍,Hank,and a pretty girl.
Strongly recommend to ppl who wants to come alone or hang out with friends to chill, date, or hv fun.
Everything are promising and just nice!

Definitely my favourite bar at Taipei. We originally went in the bar due to the wide range of quality whiskies they had to offer, then we left the place absolutely blown away by the thier cocktail making skills.

Personal favourite is Back to Better, a gin based tea infused cocktail. Knowing that we were fans of Islay whiskies, the bartender also made some delicious cocktails using the likes of Talisker Storm and Port Charlotte 10y.

Would give 6 out of 5 if I could.

Came here after our company party for the after party 😆

- Long Island iced tea and mojito
- Camille (basically pisco, sloe gin, and other stuff)
- deep fried Hiroshima oysters
- craft beers (winter melon ale and coffee stout)
- Korean fried chicken

Fun night!

Love the 1990s music played in the pub. Most customers are female. I ordered the cocktail  and mozzarella sticks. It's a nice place for solo guests, couples and groups. The aquarium above the bar table may look better from a farrer angle (fyi I sat right underneath the aquarium).

So glad I found this place! It's cozy, with great service, and pretty good drinks. Many unique ones too. My friends and I really enjoyed it, and they even gave us free shots because a small misunderstanding we had with them when making a reservation.

Will definitely be going back soon :)

Mau cari suasana unik ditengah kota ya kesini sih. Makananya khas jawa, banyak jenis makanan pedas.
Model makannya pilih makanan yg tersedia, tp bisa pesen menu dapurnya yg sering kepesan sih Mie godok dan Ayam goreng kremes. Batok telur asinnya enak
mie godog tasted okay, the lightning is too dark for my liking, but that's the essence of this place, right? 555555555
Banyak pilihan makanan. Tidak semuanya pedas, tetapi sekali makan sambelnya.. pedasny luar biasa! Tempatnya unik dan bisa untuk orang banyak.
It offers various kinds of spicy menus. The place is unique and the food tastes good, but not extraordinary. The food is kind of pricey
Konsepnya unik. Cocok buat selfie. Makannany cukul enak. Tapi kalo bawa rombongan kurang pas.
Masakan indonesia.. Nuansa jawa kental terasa.. Tempat nyaman, pegawai ramah

Nuansa jawa yang kental menghiasi restoran ini. Makanannya super enak dan seperti dirumah. Harga masih terjangkau dengan lokasi yang strategis dekat pusat keramaian di setiabudi. Kurangnya cuma parkir saja tapi tetap tidak terlalu sulit untuk didapat. Bisa pesan tunjuk seperti diwarteg bisa pesen pakai menu
Makanannya enak dan tempatnya keren ...banyak spot buat foto2
Great place for hangout, good food to eat, just a bit expensive but worth it
Outdoornya asik. Decornya keren.. Makanan beberapa B aja. Tapi jamunya enak. Outdoornya agak kurang bersih buat temen saya yang alergi debu 😅

日式同志酒吧，唱歌小酌娛樂場所！環境舒服自在讓人很放鬆！平日下班喝兩杯的好地方！

居然有水果盤招待 超驚訝

Masakannya muaacem muacem dan enak. Buat yg suka pedes dan masakan jawa versi agak elite cocok sihh. Tempatnya cukup luas jadi klo ramai jg ga umpel umpelan. Harga juga termasuk murah yaa buat restaurant di central jkt. Bolehh lah nanti makan kesini lagi klo ke jkt 🥰

Wirklich eines der besten Warungs in denen ich je war. Wer in einer kleinen Oase in der Stadt an die javanesische Küche herangeführt werden möchte, ist hier genau richtig. Alles sauber, super Service und unfassbar leckeres Essen! Das ganze Team einfach unfassbar nett. Der Besitzer hat tolle Sachen zu erzählen.Der Kaffee ist auch einfach nur lecker. Unbedingt hingehen.
nice place, heritage ambience, heritage recipes, free pisanggoreng krupuk n jamu 😊
Mantaaap mantaaapss.. Josss jossss.. Es teh nya jumbo 👍👍

Echt Javaans restaurant.

Sugeng rawuh kagem sedulur MJS.
Monggo dipun cobi daharan lan unjukanipun.

すごく良い店です!　雰囲気良いし、美味しいし、言う事なし。
ただしめっちゃ辛い、何を食べても辛い気がします。私はけっこうイケる方だと思いますが、ここは手に終えません。

review.review_text:
Another place for proper Guinness, extra cold as it should be like always!!!!
Got good food as well, bangers and mash is definitely my favourite. Highly recommended!!!!!

I never knew this place existed until a few of my foreign colleagues suggested having a gathering here. It's a wonderfully cozy pub with decent food, especially the Bangers & Mash. I can't wait to visit again!
Brilliant Bar with great food. They even did a Gluten-free Sunday Roast for my husband. What a lot of hard work Patrick and Jessica have put into this place 🥰

Lovely little pub nestled in an alleyway, out of sight from all the Taipei hustle and bustle. Stumbled upon this place and was overwhelmingly surprised. Jessica and Patrick make you feel at home. Cracking food and a creamy pint of Guinness. As an Irishman, I can testify that it’s as good as the ones in St James’ Gate. If you’re in Taipei, it’s a must visit!

Went two months ago. Wanted to order fish n chips but the server said they ran out so I had the steak pie instead. Had a sudden craving for a Sunday roast just now. Planned to go this Sunday, and saw a comment 3 days ago that they no longer serve Sunday roast. I’m making a request of the smiths please, please, please let me get what I want for this bar 🤣🤣 and I’ll keep going and trying to get what I want in my first attempt lol. Great food, atmosphere, and music by the way! 👍🏽👍🏽

Superb food, been in Tapei two weeks and eaten here 5 times. Excellent service and excellent quality food and drink.  Having spent last 10 years in SE Asia. This is the best Western food at reasonable prices I have found anywhere.  Many thanks guys.

It’s a very nice place for visiting friends or for family’s happy hours. The English and Scottish foods are quite good. The beef is favorable and the fish and chips is so great. Also the music inside the restaurant was played is nostalgic 80s style. Very nice. It’s a very good choice for people to have a good dinner time in city center.

My new favorite place for happy hour
In Taipei.
I had the fish and chips and it was perfect. Chef cooked chips(fries) nice and crispy. Had all the best condiments
Ketchup, Tobasco and malt vinegar in bottles not packets. Well done
I'll be back for happy hour beer(s) and bangers TONIGHT! Monday special.

Christmas dinner was fantastic
My compliments to chef and manager
PERFECT evening
Thank You

Delicious food. I like the food more than drinks! The brownies with ice cream is fantastic. You can play board games, darts and some other games for free. Just grab a drink and chill out here. Reasonable price. I will come here again for the brownie 👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽

One of the best pubs with pub and Scottish food. The portions are quite generous, there is happy hour abd it's not overcrowded but quite comfortable.  Whenever I have s craving for bangers abd mash, I head down to Aye Taipei.

Tempat makan di setiabudi, ambiencenya oke, tradisional, harga sesuai dengan rasa makanan. Catatan untuk resto, apabila pemesanan dalam jumlah banyak dan beberapa keluarga, seharusnya ordernya bisa dipisah, tidak digabung, sehingga akan bingung nantinya.

Pelayanan cukup cepat, ambience sejuk.

Restoran jawa dengan berbagai menu khas jawa. Bagi orang jawa yg merantau di jakarta, sangat disarankan nyoba makan disini. Menunya banyak, menu2 tradisional. Interior ruangan tradisional banget, berasa lagi di jogja. Harga cukup terjangkau. Saat makan malam sangat ramai, jadi saya sarankan reservasi dulu.
Makanannya enak semua, pelayanannya juga baik dan ramah, suasana tempatnya menarik, "feels like home", memang parkirnya terbatas tapi ada valet, jadi gak perlu khawatir
Suasana tempatnya terbilang bagus bernuansa Jawa. Pelayanannya cukup memuaskan cuma kalo bisa disediakan daftar menu makanan & minuman bagi setiap tamu yang datang.
Aneka makanan rumahan yang biasa didapatkan  di Warteg, namun dengan rasa makanan lebih otentik dan enak. Interior yang bernuansa jawa.

tempatnya nyaman,luas,lucu pula, jadi enak buat kumpul santai bareng keluarga atau kolega. menunya adalah masakan jawa jadi rasanya lebih ke manis,buat orang jawa kayak saya pas banget lah dan bisa buat ngobatin rasa kangen masakan jawa kalo di jakarta. ada mushola nya juga jadi bisa tenang kalo mau lama disitu. recommended lah,dan bakal mau kesini berkali-kali lagi. aksesnya jg gampang,ada tempat parkir juga,tapi untuk motor di tempatkan di sebrang tempat makan.

sangat banyak variasi makanannya, rasanya enak2, pelayanannya memuaskan. Saran saya tolong diadakan daftar menunya biar pelanggan yg dateng bisa order lewat menu tanpa harus pelayanannya jelasin satu2 biar klo pas ramai tidak menjadi antri panjang
Semua makanannya enak, tp mayoritas spicy, jd prefer nanya dulu sm waiternya, apakh menu yg kita mau pedas atau nggak, favorit sih telur dadar, per ayam an dan lodeh tempenya 🥰
Makanannya enak2 sih. But a little bit pricey yaa. Sama ayamnya enak sih spicy. Cm personally lebih prefer digoreng ayamnya. Lebih tasty
Mantap tempatnya, tradisional banget. Cuman memang makanan masih biasa dan parkiran masih kurang

review.review_text: The food has been getting better and better over the years. Tonight I tried the Monkey burger and I was blown away. This was one of the best burgers I’ve had in a long while. The beef patty was so flavorful and juicy, wow! The bun and salad were fresh and the fries were delicious. I’m going back for more soon!

A bar for expats who want a feeling of home away from home the good old days type of feel with wide selection of draft beers as well as micro breweries craft beers but the only gripe I have is the gravy fries with cheese is actually chili cheese fries in English

Came in with my wife and 13 month old son around 630 pm. The staff, Especially Lynn was amazing and super attentive and helped entertain our son while we tried to look at the menu.   Through out our visit Lynn took care of us and made sure we had everything we needed and our little man was happy. Absolutely recommend and enjoyed this spot.

Very nice American/Canadian style bar.  Fantastic prices and great selection of food.  Good, honest, bar food.

Crowd is a mix of expats and locals and people are not shy to hit the dance floor.  They have a pool table as well.

Over from Qld Australia and right from the start emailing to make a reservation for dinner and to watch The State of Origin match responce was quick and friendly from Alex.
What a great place, great food, staff and atmosphere. When we arrived, Alex greeted us and made us very welcomed.
Thanks Brass Monkey for a great night.

Been here multiple times and always enjoyed it. Great choice of beers including IPA and other forms which most bars in Taiwan don't have. food menu is extensive and genuinely good. service can be a bit variable, I usually find the waitresses a bit lethargic, but the gent behind the bar counter is very responsive and helpful.

This is a great sports bar with a great selection of craft beers.  In addition, the food here is pretty amazing.  I had an order of chili chips and I gotta say the chili tasted the same as the ones I had in Los Angeles. In addition, the staff is amazing, highly recommended.

Great staff, amazing service.  Comprehensive menu that hits on all the categories, even the vegetarian items are a home run.   Highly suggest that if you are in town and want some comfort food to hit them up.  Don’t like to give out out all 5’s often but Brass Monkey works hard to keep them!

Absolutely great place if you like to eat, dance , drink, make friends

The atmosphere on Tuesday is very nice
It is a Salsa dance time
Everything start at 9 pm but more people come around 10 pm

It is a lovely place to go to after work :)

Very good music. They have a schedule for events and Thursday 1/19 is Qi Pao night and free entry for all ladies with free drinks all night (not shots). Very professional waiters and waitresses. The space is an open space with little tables. Further inside is a table of pool and darts. And the bathroom is significantly clean!
Tempat makan yg rekomendasi sekali dan wajib utk didatangi bersama keluarga atau teman krna mknannya enak2 dan suasana yg unik.
pilihan makanan super banyak dan enak. Desain restonya unik. Kerupuknya free!!! Ambil sepuasnya

Mi and my familia so enjoyed.
makanan enak..anak2 suka ..thx
Makanannya enak, kemarin ada kesalahan kelebihan bayar, dikembalikan sih cuma klo take away harus dicek sendiri supaya ga bolak balik complain

For those, who like Indonesian cuisine, MJS can be an option.

Before the pandemic era, the MJS is a place to stop by waiting for 3in1. now maybe it will be a different story because it has turned into odd-even.

Its vintage concept with a traditional Javanese atmosphere instantly makes the heart feel comfortable. The presentation of okulele and bass sounds as residence music. Make u feel like home.

For the price it depends on how much you want to eat, but what is clear is that it won't be more expensive than eating at pizza hut or fast food restaurants.

the place is quite large for "Warung", it is popular for groups to had the sspecial occasion here. For large groups you have to book in advance to be able to dine in here.
The food is average, and the service is ok. The indoor seating area had many rooms since it seems this place used to be a residential home. This place has many artistic articles such as statue wall decoration

Back again after more than 3 or 4 year i guess..

Cant find the iconic statue anymore, and also there's some change in the restaurant name.
But for the food. A real heaven for a super spicy fans. But dont worry they also serve the non spicy one.

About the price,, they maintain it level with other dining or lunch places around the CBD area.

One of the best places (with their unique, ethnic and rustic ambiences) for a big group of friend or fams.

Ohya, they still doing a live music at dinner time. Really suit and support the ambience there.
Buat orang jakarta masakan Jawa cukup komplit di sini

review.review_text: Amazing atmosphere, highly attentive staff that know their game, the bartender was super nice and made suggestions as to which beer to go with. I bought some to bring home and got some freebies too. Beer are rather expensive but worth the price.

First and foremost this place is INCREDIBLE. Once we walked in the staff were super friendly, best way I can describe it was walking in to CHEERS ( It’s an American 🇺🇸 thing - 😜 ). Yes, they speak English and will help you in your beer selection. If you are a beer connoisseur, this is your heaven. OMG, the selection is endless, but please note the staff is knowledgeable and helpful in helping you navigate the process of satisfying your palate. Definitely take a moment to visit this incredible place.

Amazingly delicious beer. My favorite is the Jasmine Session Ale (from Taiwan head brewers).. like a light pale ale with a strong jasmine flavor. They nailed it, just incredible beer. The Dong Ding oolong tea ale is also very good, and the Jin Xuan Rain water tea ale is a very unique brown ale.

But very expensive $$$ though (and I'm from New York City!) Like my first visit, I ordered 1 large and 1 small draft beer, and paid $832 TWD, plus a 5% fee for paying with credit card. That's almost $30 USD for one small 10oz beer, and one 500mL beer!! That's double the price you pay at some of the best breweries in NYC, and around the world.

For the brewery experience (which imo is just as, if not more, important as the actual beer).. initially had a misunderstanding w the owner, but we cleared the air. And since then I have been back 6 more times (even 2 days in a row). I even brought 2 of my coworkers here, and I've now tried over 10 beers..and no surprise, all were excellent. So I will keep coming back, because the beers are awesome and both Ida and Susie have been very welcoming. The food is also good (I've tried a few dishes so far).

So overall, the beer is amazing, and the people are nice.. but very high prices. But I'll still come back because the beers are excellent, and I like the people. But seriously, bring cash!! (because funk that 5% visa charge)
Great selection of beers and amazing service! Especially loved the barrel aged cherry sour ! Highly recommend coming here.
Amazing selection of beers. Had am imperial stout, tasted amazing. Also a great vibe and service!
The beer is AMAZING! It’s the best beer I have had since leaving California. Bartender speaks great English and there is a nice atmosphere.

Popped in on Lunar new year eve right at opening and was greeted by the owner.  We enjoyed a number of craft beers, the Taiwan session ale Oolong was definitely my favorite.  It was nice to see such a nice selection of beers.  We ordered some food, a salad and some popcorn chicken.  The wasabi salad was quite tasty and we actually kept the left over salad dressing as a dipping sauce for the popcorn chicken.  Tasty. We enjoyed the ambience, the brief chats and recommendations by the owner, who was very friendly.  We appreciate the hospitality.
Love the way they celebrate the festival 🎊🎉🎄👍🏻 The foods are just nice for pairing for the craft beer in Taipei 💪

Stopped in for a quick beer before heading to the airport.
For a Friday afternoon, it was pretty quiet. I got to try another local brewery (Redpoint brewing), and it was nice, a good, balanced IPA.
The tap list was a bit depleted, but still had a few interesting beers, plus a fridge full of a variety of stuff.
Service was a bit aloof, but that was okay.
I don't think they have a bathroom, or if they do it's behind the kitchen and couldn't see it.

Pretty misleading name. I was walking by and the risotto got my attention. There was someone standing outside and they pressured me to come in. They recommended me the mushroom risotto saying it was really good so I went with it.

It wasn't risotto. It was mostly just mushrooms and rice. 1/5

The thing that was pretty good was the roasted marshmallow match latte. Roasted marshmallows are good in any situation. 4/5

The service was nice and attentive (but fully clothed...did not impact the score).

I'm surprised the reviews are so high for this place since the food is a little pricey and very plain. Lots of these reviewers only have 1 review and it's for this place for 5 stars. I'm sure you can earn 5 stars, just focus on quality.
Oseng lidah nya lezat sekali. Botok telur asin nya menetralisir makanan pedas. Suka.
Authentic Indonesia's cuisine served with local's drinks and snacks. Make sure you do the booking before dine in, as this place normally packed with people (especially during lunch time)

Akses mudah pinggir jalan. Begitu masuk wangi kaya dupa, trus menunya, cuman saran aja lebih bagus pakai kaca ya untuk menunya kalau pake plastik agak burek gitu jd keliatannya kurang bersih. Suasana indoor nya sumpek, pengap, jd pilih yg outdoor, tp banyak tikusnya karena saya takut banget sama tikus jadi parno makan sambil naikin kaki ke kursi. Karena liat ada tikus muncul2 di bawah jembatan diatas kolam renang, trus ada suara2 curut sama banyak jebakan tikus, jd was2 banget. Toiletnya juga gelap kurang bersih. Untuk makanan ya lumayan beragam pilihannya untuk rasa biasa saja, ayam bakar dan ayam gorengnya keras. Semoga bisa lebih baik. Terimakasih
Rasa dan tempatnya enakkk! Kalo pulang dari sini jangan lupa ngebungkus kopinya, enaaaaak. Ambience nya jawa bangett dapet, dihibur juga ada nyanyian live music jawa 👍🏻👍🏻

Sekian lama baru tahu kalo ditengah kota jakarta di wilayah kuningan ad rumah makan dengan model yg etnic seperti ini.

Kalau di lihat dari luar, rumah makan ini hanya kelihatan kecil,tetapi ternyata salah. Begitu luas area di dalam nya. Terbagi buat yg suka merokok maupun yg di ruang ac

Masuk ke awal kita disambut dengan pramusaji yang menggunakan blankon (jawa bgt ya), di kiri kanan bisa kita lihat banyak sekali hiasan2 yg ad disekeliling nya. Oya ad jamu penyegar juga lho diberikan gratis buat pengunjung yang datang. Di area tengah akan kita temukan berbagai ornamen2  etnik, ad juga kopi kekinian. Tak lupa hiburan keroncongan juga ad disana, siap menghibur tamu yg datang. Dibagian belakang makin rame lagi dgn ornamen macam2, spot yg bagus buat berpoto3. Yuks ajak keluarga kita mampir kesana, dijamim seru, senang dan kenyang

Tolonf berikan 👍jika anda suka dengan ulasan ini
restoran yang unik, dengan makanan khas jawa sebagai makanan utama. desain resto dengan banyak ornamen klasik. membangkitkan suasana tempo dulu.

This is a hidden treasure cove in the bustle of the city. There is a lot of similarity in the food and the ambience. Both are brimming with surprises and have a lot to explore.
Some interesting choices for vegetarians too.
Home cooked Javanese food served in a splendid ambience. Must visit if you happen to be in Jakarta. I hear it's a one of a kind restaurant.

Adem, family friendly, tradisional nan sendu. Makanan enak. Masukan saja utk kolam di sekitar, mesti lebih sering dibersihkan, spya nyamuk2 tdk nempel ke kaki tamu. Hehe. Overall enak, ramai, banyak pilihan, sambelnya pedas, bapak yg nyanyi jg adem suaranya (fyi: jgn lupa utk mengapresiasi seikhlasnya bapak yg menyanyikan tembang merdu dan memainkan alat musik dgn apik yah). Cakep deh

Urusan rasa makanan sih juaranya
Harga jg sangat bertanggung jawab :D
Tp karena memang konsep tempatnya artsy2 javanese gitu, jd banyak ornamen2 unik n anehh. Sampe tetiba ada sesisir pisang digantung di atas kepala :D

Selalu ngangenin dan recommended! Sampe selalu lupa foto2.

Tempat yg nyaman utk Nongkrong baik dengan keluarga atau teman. Outdoorsnya sangat Instagramable banget. Cuman kalau datang di jam makan dan ingin duduk di outdoor kadang harus menunggu karena penuh. Utk rasa makanan cukup enak. Harga sesuai. Minuman beragam...

review.review_text: The bar had a really nice ambience and the drinks were really good! Also, the staff were really nice! I could not remember his name but he helped us book a taxi since our Uber was not working. I really appreciate the help and will definitely come back here when we visit Taipei again!

Stumbled upon this place on a random Monday night! So fun with interesting drinks. We got the Sherlock Holmes, Romeo and Juliet and the fries. All delicious and the service was great (English available)

A cute novel themed bar with a very strange drink menu. I had the Percy Jackson drink. It was so weird but also good. The staff was very enthusiastic and helped us pick drinks. The decor is fun and cozy. The music wasn't so loud that you could have conversations. It was a wonderful place to have a drink with friends.

The beverages are superb; I opted for Romeo and Juliet & the Chronicles of Narnia. The flavors are exquisite, and I truly enjoy them. Additionally, the atmosphere and service are fantastic. Kirin, and Wednesday, our servers, is exceptionally friendly and welcoming. Even after their relocation, we will certainly revisit.

Beautiful hole in the wall bar in Taipei! The bar has an interesting concept with an unassuming store front which opens up into a Harry Potter like atmosphere. Drinks were interesting & ambience is great for chatting as well since music is not that loud. 👍🏻

Creative and tasty drinks in a comfortable and elegant spot! So many signature drinks named after big fantasy novels, and many others inspired by local Taiwanese ingredients and foods. And their team is amazing.

I had a blast here with a crew of 8 friends from the US and UK! Their team spoke English and was super friendly and accommodating, carefully explaining the menu when we asked and making adjustments to fit our preferences.

this speakeasy bar got good food and drinks - i especially like how they were all named with creativity! went there for a drink at 7pm when it just opened, so not many people were there. staff were friendly and helpful too 💯

may need to figure out how to get the door open, but remember it’s a BOOK themed bar!

review.review_text: This bar is really cute and has tons of space. We tried a lot of their beers and they were all great. I really enjoyed their fruit ales as they are very sweet.

First time having drinks here. Last time I went to Taihu near Taipei City Hall station.

The atmosphere in Ximenting was awesome. Background music wasn’t too loud. Seats are comfortable. And the location was 5 minutes from the MRT.

We ordered Taihu Son of Grape island, Taihu Kumquat, and Taihu draft high. My favourite beer is Taihu Kumquat among all these three.

To friendship! 🍻 This place is worthy to visit.

Very busy but great atmosphere. Wonderful selection of beer and cocktails on tap. Kudos to the staff who were managing the floor at its busiest but still reaching out to each and every customer. Great front of house hospitality. Initially had a standing table but was quickly moved to a seated table. Looking forward to come again!

The bartenders and staff went above and beyond to make me feel comfortable.  I had some of my fondest memory of my trip at the bar in Driftwood Taihu.  Their unique beer selection boasts a variety of taste that any style of beer drinker will enjoy.  Be sure to ask for 高梁 as that's the drink of choice for most of the staff and earns you extra kudo points!

Excellent local beers, some of the best beer we had on our trip to Taiwan. Bartenders were really friendly and efficient and patient with us. Beer can be a bit more pricey than other places but you’re paying for craft and quality. We arrived too late to try any food sadly so can’t comment on food

review.review_text: This is a brewpub, with their own beers/ales. The IPA is niiiice. Nearly 10 years in operation. 3/16/2024 is their anniversary, and expect related activities.

Very good environment and music are good! Love the place, the best part is guest stay with Papa Whale Hotel get a small glass of drink when you purchase a drink. So, it’s a Buy 1 Free 1 drink being the hotel guest.

Very good!!! Love it!!!

Their cocktails are so special. They have a lot of flavours for you to choose. I just try the urchin one. God, the taste is so great!

The cocktail here is so delicate and delicious. Minimal design with lots well balance flavors. I love they don’t do crazy decoration or fancy presentation. Its slick and pure. Small portion, almost feel like drinking really good high mountain tea. Love their mocktails too, it made me feel like I am drinking good cocktails. Awesome place.

The place looks like a small restaurant from upfront, with its small parking space, but once you got in you'll be surprised. But hey don't worry about parking, they provide FREE valet service.
The place, is a refurbished old house, they kept most of the essentials as it was such as doors,walls and high ceiling. Inside is like a time machine full of trinkets from time gone by, I had so much fun with my daughter, she was trying to guess every odd thing she saw here (imagine how to explain a stamp for the new generations). There's a set of Javanese puppet dolls (wayang kulit), a collection of baseball caps, butterfly collections, etc.
The food is tasty! They use only free ranged chicken, cooked well, not to crispy but the seasoning sipped well into the meat. Seriously lots of selection of food! What I don't recommend is the krecek. The rest like, selections of chickens, ducks, lungs (yes cow's lung), Tempe,tofu, ribs, meat soup, and all other selection my big fan ordered, were good!
My family was seated in semi outdoor seating, in front of the coffee stall,which I think is the best seat to listen to the life music of traditional Javanese songs and easy to order drinks and food. They have outdoor seating near the shallow pool at the back.
I really recommend this place for you who want to feel a bit of Javanese culture such as food and songs (tembang).
